\h 1 Chronicles
\toc1 1 Chronicles
\toc2 1 Chronicles
\toc3 1 Chr.
\mt2 The first
\mt1 Sequential Account
\mt2 (1 Chronicles)
\is1 Introduction
\ip The \bk First\bk* and the \bk Second Account of Chronicles\bk* are a retelling of lots of what's included in \bk The accounts about Shemuel (Samuel)\bk* and of \bk The accounts about the kings\bk*, but told in different words. There seem to be two primary purposes for this account:
\ip 1. So that the reader can learn more about the destruction of Yehudah (Judah) and Yisrael (Israel), as God fulfilled his promise and plans for his people. This writer illustrates the achievements of David, Shelomoh (Solomon), of Yehoshafat (Jehoshaphat), Hizkiyah (Hezekiah), of Yoshiyah (Josiah), along with other people who obeyed Yahweh's instructions.
\ip 2. To document the division of the priests and Levites in preparation for their service in the soon-to-be-built temple for Yahweh, and the extensive preparations by King David that were eventually handed over to King Shelomoh. Yahweh had carefully instructed David about how he wanted the temple worship to operate, and then this was all written down and handed over to Shelomoh, who would be the one who would go on to construct the buildings and all the furnishings and equipment and utensils that were required for its functioning.
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Lists of the ancestors \ior 1:1вҖ“9:44\ior*
\io1 King Shaul's death \ior 10:1-14\ior*
\io1 David's kingdom \ior 11:1вҖ“29:30\ior*
\io2 a. Wars and victories \ior 11:1вҖ“22:1\ior*
\io2 b. Preparation for the temple construction \ior 22:2вҖ“29:30\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Adam's descendants
\rem /s1 Historical Records From Adam to Abraham; From Adam to Abraham; From Adam to Saul; From Adam to Noah's Sons
\r (Gen. 5:1-32; 10:1-32; 11:10-26)
\rem /s2 To Noah's Sons
\p
\v 1 Adam, Shet \add (SethВҰ187052)\add*, EnoshВҰ187053,
\v 2 Kenan, MahalalelВҰ187056, YaredВҰ187057 \add (Jared)\add*,
\v 3 Hanok \add (Enoch)\add*, Metushelah \add (MethuselahВҰ187060)\add*, LamekВҰ187061,
\v 4 Noah, ShemВҰ187064, HamВҰ187065, andВҰ187066 YafetВҰ187066 \add (Japeth)\add*.
\rem /s1 Descendants of Japheth
\rem /s2 The Japhethites
\p
\v 5 Yafet's sonsВҰ187069 were GomerВҰ187071, MagogВҰ187072, MadayВҰ187073, YavanВҰ187074, Tuval, MeshekВҰ187076, and TirasВҰ187077.
\v 6 Gomer'sВҰ187081 sonsВҰ187080 were AshkenazВҰ187082, RifatВҰ187083, and TogarmahВҰ187084.
\v 7 Yavan'sВҰ187087 sonsВҰ187086 were ElishahВҰ187088, TarshishВҰ187089, KittimВҰ187090, andВҰ187086 RodanimВҰ187091.
\rem /s1 Descendants of Ham
\rem /s2 The Hamites
\p
\v 8 Ham'sВҰ187095 sonsВҰ187094 were Kush, Mitsrayim, PutВҰ187098, and KanaanВҰ187099.
\v 9 Kush's sons were SebaВҰ187103, HavilahВҰ187104, SabtaВҰ187105, Raamah, and Savteka. Raamah'sВҰ187109 sons were Sheva and DedanВҰ187111.
\v 10 Then KushВҰ187114 fatheredВҰ187115 NimrodВҰ187118 \add and\add* he became a mightyВҰ187122 \add warrior\add*.
\v 11 Mitsrayim was the ancestor of the Lud, the AnamВҰ187134, the LehabВҰ187137, the NaftuhВҰ187140,
\v 12 the PatrusВҰ187144, the Kasluh, andВҰ187142 the KaftorВҰ187154 people groups. (The PhilistinesВҰ187151 descended from the Kasluh people group.)
\v 13 Kanaan'sВҰ187157 firstВҰ187162 son was Tsidon, and then \add вүҲheВҰ187158 was also the ancestor of the Hittites\add*,
\v 14 the YebusitesВҰ187169, the AmoritesВҰ187172, the GirgashitesВҰ187174,
\v 15 the HivitesВҰ187178, the ArkitesВҰ187181, the SinitesВҰ187184,
\v 16 the ArvaditesВҰ187188, the ZemaritesВҰ187191, andВҰ187186 the HamatitesВҰ187194.
\rem /s1 Descendants of Shem
\rem /s2 The Semites
\p
\v 17 Shem'sВҰ187198 sons were ElamВҰ187199, Ashur, ArpakshadВҰ187201, LudВҰ187202, and Aram. \add Aram'sВҰ187203 sons were\add*: Uts, HulВҰ187205, GeterВҰ187206, and MeshekВҰ187207.
\v 18 ArpakshadВҰ187210 was the father of Shelah, and Shelah was the father of EberВҰ187219.
\v 19 Eber had twoВҰ187223 sonsВҰ187224: PelegВҰ187227 (\add which sounds like the Hebrew word for вҖҳdividedвҖҷ\add*, because in his lifetime, the earthВҰ187231 was divided)\x + \xo 1:19 \xt Gen 11:1-9.\x* andВҰ187221 YoktanВҰ187234.
\v 20 Yoktan was the ancestor of: AlmodadВҰ187240, ShelefВҰ187243, Hatsarmavet, YerahВҰ187249,
\v 21 HadoramВҰ187253, UzalВҰ187256, DiklahВҰ187259,
\v 22 Eybal, AbimaelВҰ187266, Sheva,
\v 23 OfirВҰ187273, HavilahВҰ187276, andВҰ187271 Yovav. All those were the descendants of YoktanВҰ187284.
\p
\v 24 \add These were the descendants of\add* ShemВҰ187287 \add (in order from him to Abraham)\add*: Arpakshad, ShelahВҰ187290,
\v 25 Eber, PelegВҰ187293, ReuВҰ187294,
\v 26 Serug, NahorВҰ187297, TerahВҰ187298,
\v 27 and Abram (\add whose name God later changed to\add* AbrahamВҰ187302).
\s1 Yishmael's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Abraham; From Abraham to Jacob; The Family of Abraham; The Descendants of Ishmael
\r (Gen. 25:12-16)
\p
\v 28 Abraham'sВҰ187306 sonsВҰ187305 were Yitshak \add (IsaacВҰ187307)\add* andВҰ187308 YishmaelВҰ187308 \add (Ishmael)\add*.
\rem /s2 Descendants of Hagar
\v 29 These were theirВҰ187312 family lines: The firstВҰ187313 son born to YishmaelВҰ187314 \add (the son of Abraham's slave-wife Hagar)\add* was Nevayot, then his other sons KedarВҰ187316, AdbeelВҰ187317, MibsamВҰ187318,
\v 30 MishmaВҰ187320, DumahВҰ187321, MassaВҰ187322, HadadВҰ187323, TemaВҰ187324,
\v 31 Yetur, NafishВҰ187327, andВҰ187328 KedemahВҰ187328. Those were Yishmael'sВҰ187332 \add twelve\add* sonsВҰ187331.
\rem /s2 Descendants of Keturah
\v 32 The sons of Abraham'sВҰ187338 slave-wife KeturahВҰ187336 were ZimranВҰ187342, Yokshan, MedanВҰ187344, Midyan, YishbakВҰ187346, and ShuahВҰ187347. Yokshan'sВҰ187343 sons were Sheva and DedanВҰ187351.
\v 33 Midyan's sons were EfahВҰ187356, EferВҰ187357, Hanok, AbidaВҰ187359, and EldaahВҰ187360. All those were Keturah'sВҰ187365 descendants.
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Esau; Descendants of Isaac
\rem /s2 Descendants of Sarah
\rem /r (Genesis 36.1-19)
\p
\v 34 AbrahamВҰ187369 had his son Yitshak \add by his wife Sarah\add*, and Yitshak's sonsВҰ187374 were EsauВҰ187376 and \add Yakov, whose name God later changed to\add* YisraelВҰ187377 \add (IsraelВҰ187377)\add*.
\s1 Esau's descendants
\rem /s1 Esau's Sons; Descendants of Esau
\r (Gen. 36:1-19)
\p
\v 35 Esau'sВҰ187381 sonsВҰ187380 were ElifazВҰ187382, ReuelВҰ187383, YeushВҰ187384, YalamВҰ187385, and KorahВҰ187386.
\v 36 Elifaz'sВҰ187390 sonsВҰ187389 were TemanВҰ187391, OmarВҰ187392, TsefoВҰ187393, GatamВҰ187394, KenazВҰ187395, TimnaВҰ187396, and AmalekВҰ187397.
\v 37 Reuel'sВҰ187401 sonsВҰ187400 were NahatВҰ187402, ZerahВҰ187403, ShammahВҰ187404, andВҰ187405 MizzahВҰ187405.
\s1 Seir's descendants
\rem /s1 Original Peoples of Edom; The Original Inhabitants of Edom
\r (Gen. 36:20-30)
\rem /s2 The People of Seir in Edom
\p
\v 38 SeirВҰ187409 \add was another descendant of Esau, and his\add* sonsВҰ187408 were LotanВҰ187410, ShovalВҰ187411, Tsiveon, AnahВҰ187413, DishonВҰ187414, Etser, and DishanВҰ187416.
\rem /s1 The Kings of Edom
\rem /r (Genesis 36.31-43)
\v 39 Lotan's sonsВҰ187418 were HoriВҰ187420 and HomamВҰ187421, and Lotan's sisterВҰ187422 was TimnaВҰ187424.
\v 40 Shoval's sons were AlyanВҰ187429, ManahatВҰ187430, Eyval, ShefoВҰ187432, and OnamВҰ187433. Tsiveon's sons were Ayyah and AnahВҰ187438.
\v 41 Anah'sВҰ187441 son was Dishon. Dishon'sВҰ187442 sons were HamranВҰ187446, EshbanВҰ187447, IthranВҰ187448, and KeranВҰ187449.
\v 42 Etser's sons were BilhanВҰ187455, ZaavanВҰ187456, and YaakanВҰ187457. Dishan's sons were Uts and AranВҰ187461.
\s1 Edom's rulers
\rem /s1 Rulers of Edom
\r (Gen. 36:31-43)
\rem /s2 The Rulers of Edom
\p
\v 43 These are the kings who ruled the region of EdomВҰ187469 \add (where Seir's descendants lived)\add* before any kings ruled over YisraelВҰ187475: BelaВҰ187476 son of BeorВҰ187479, and his city's name was Dinhavah.
\v 44 When BelaВҰ187485 diedВҰ187484, Zerah'sВҰ187491 son Yovav from Batsrah \add city\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\v 45 When Yovav diedВҰ187494, HushamВҰ187498 \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*. He was from the region where the Teman people group lived.
\v 46 When HushamВҰ187503 diedВҰ187502, Bedad'sВҰ187509 son Hadad \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*. His city's nameВҰ187516 was AvitВҰ187518. Hadad defeatedВҰ187510 the Midyan people group in the MoabВҰ187515 region.
\v 47 When HadadВҰ187522 diedВҰ187521, SamlahВҰ187525 from MasrekahВҰ187526 \add city\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\v 48 WhenВҰ187533 SamlahВҰ187529 diedВҰ187528, ShaulВҰ187532 from Rehovot-on-the-river \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\v 49 When ShaulВҰ187537 diedВҰ187536, Akbor's son Baal-HananВҰ187541 \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\v 50 When Baal-HananВҰ187548 died, HadadВҰ187551 \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*. His city's name was Pa'u. His wife's name was MeheytavelвҖ”she was the daughter of MatredВҰ187560 \add вүҲandВҰ187546 the granddaughter\add* of Me-ZahabВҰ187563.
\p
\v 51 ThenВҰ187565 HadadВҰ187566\x + \xo 1:51 \xt 1:46.\x* diedВҰ187565.
\p The leaders of the EdomВҰ187570 people group were Chiefs TimnaВҰ187572, AlvahВҰ187574, Yetet,
\v 52 AholivamahВҰ187580, ElahВҰ187582, PinonВҰ187584,
\v 53 KenazВҰ187587, TemanВҰ187589, MivtsarВҰ187591,
\v 54 MagdielВҰ187594, and IramВҰ187596. Those were the chiefsВҰ187595 of EdomВҰ187599.
\c 2
\s1 Yakob's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Judah; Descendants of Israel; The Sons of Israel and the Descendants of Judah; Israel's Sons
\p
\v 1 These were Yisrael's sonsВҰ187603: ReuvenВҰ187605, Shimeon \add (SimeonВҰ187606)\add*, LeviВҰ187607, and Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*, Yissakar \add (IssacharВҰ187609)\add*, and ZebulunВҰ187610,
\v 2 Dan, YosefВҰ187613 \add (Joseph)\add*, BenyaminВҰ187614, NaftaliВҰ187615, GadВҰ187616, and AsherВҰ187617.
\s1 Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 Judah; Descendants of Judah
\rem /s2 To Hezron's Sons
\p
\v 3 Yehudah's sons (with the CanaaniteВҰ187631 woman Bat-Shua) were Er, and OnanВҰ187623, and ShelahВҰ187624. (Yehudah's eldest son, Er, was evil in Yahweh's eyesВҰ187638, and he killed him.)
\v 4 His daughter-in-law TamarВҰ187643 had \add twin boys named\add* Perets and ZerahВҰ187652, so altogether YehudahВҰ187656 had fiveВҰ187657 sonsВҰ187655.
\p
\v 5 Perets's sonsВҰ187660 were Hetsron andВҰ187664 HamulВҰ187664.
\v 6 ZerahВҰ187668 had fiveВҰ187675 sonsВҰ187667: ZimriВҰ187669, Eytan, Heyman, KalkolВҰ187672, and DaraВҰ187673.
\v 7 \add Zimri had a son named Karmi.\add* Karmi had a son named Akar who brought troubleВҰ187681 into YisraelВҰ187682 \add вүҲby violating a ban\add* on devotedВҰ187685 thingsВҰ187685.\x + \xo 2:7: \xt Josh 7:1.\x*
\v 8 Eytan'sВҰ187689 son was AzaryahВҰ187690.
\s1 King David's ancestors
\rem /s1 The Family Tree of King David; From Judah's Grandson Hezron to David
\p
\v 9 Hetsron had three sonsВҰ187692: Yerahme'elВҰ187700, RamВҰ187703, andВҰ187692 Keluvay.\f + \fr 2:9 \ft In the Hebrew, вҖҳKeluvayвҖҷ is called вҖҳKalevвҖҷ (Caleb) below.\f*
\rem /s2 From Ram Son of Hezron
\p
\v 10 Ram was the father of Amminadav, andВҰ187713 Amminadav was the father of NahshonВҰ187717вҖ”a leaderВҰ187718 of the \add вүҲtribe\add* of YehudahВҰ187720.
\v 11 Nahshon was the father of Salma. Salma was the father of BoazВҰ187731.
\v 12 Boaz was the father of Oved. Oved was the father of YishayВҰ187742 \add (Jesse)\add*.
\v 13 YishayВҰ187744 had his son EliavВҰ187751 firstВҰ187748, AbinadabВҰ187752 secondВҰ187753, ShimeaВҰ187754 thirdВҰ187755.
\v 14 Netanel fourthВҰ187758, RaddaiВҰ187759 fifthВҰ187760,
\v 15 Otsem sixthВҰ187763, then DavidВҰ187764 \add вүҲlast\add*.
\v 16 Their sistersВҰ187767 were Tseruyah and Avigayil. Tseruyah's threeВҰ187778 sonsВҰ187771 were Avshai, Yoav \add (Joab)\add*, and Asah'el.
\v 17 Avigayil had Amasa. Amasa'sВҰ187784 fatherВҰ187785 was YeterВҰ187787, a descendant of YishmaelВҰ187788 \add (Ishmael)\add*.
\s1 The descendants of Kalev (Caleb)
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Hezron; Descendants of Hezron's Son Caleb
\rem /s2 Caleb Son of Hezron
\p
\v 18 Hetsron's \add third\add* son Kalev \add (Caleb)\add* had sons with Azuvah, one of his wives. The sons were YesherВҰ187804, Shovav, andВҰ187790 ArdonВҰ187806. (The other wife's name was Yeriot.)
\v 19 When Azuvah diedВҰ187808, Kalev married Efrat, andВҰ187808 they had a son named HurВҰ187821.
\v 20 Hur was the father of Uri, andВҰ187828 Uri was the father of Betsal'el.
\p
\v 21 Later, when Hetsron was sixtyВҰ187850 years old, he \add вүҲhad sexual intercourse\add* with a daughterВҰ187840 of MakirВҰ187842 from the region of GileadВҰ187844 and marriedВҰ187846 her. \add @Hetsron's new wife\add* gaveВҰ187852 birthВҰ187852 to \add their son\add* Seguv.
\v 22 Seguv was the fatherВҰ187859 of Yair, andВҰ187858 Yair controlled twenty-three citiesВҰ187868 in the GileadВҰ187870 region.
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ187872\add* GeshurВҰ187873 and AramВҰ187875 captured Havvot-YairВҰ187879 and KenatВҰ187883 from them, plus \add вүҲtheir surrounding towns\add*вҖ”sixtyВҰ187887 towns \add in all,\add* \add вүҲpopulated by\add* descendants of MakirВҰ187893 (the fatherВҰ187894 of GileadВҰ187896).
\v 24 After Hetsron's deathВҰ187899 in Kalev-Efratah, his wifeВҰ187904 Aviyyah gaveВҰ187907 birthВҰ187907 to his son AshhurВҰ187911, the fatherВҰ187912 of TekoaВҰ187913.
\s1 Yerahme'el's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Hezron's Son Jerahmeel; The Descendants of Jerahmeel
\rem /s2 Jerahmeel Son of Hezron
\p
\v 25 Hetsron's oldest son was Yerahme'el \add and\add* his sonsВҰ187916 were RamВҰ187923 (the oldest), BunahВҰ187924, OrenВҰ187925, Otsem, and Ahiyyah.
\v 26 Yerahme'el had anotherВҰ187931 wifeВҰ187930 named AtarahВҰ187934. She was the motherВҰ187936 of OnamВҰ187937.
\v 27 The sonsВҰ187941 of Yerahme'el's oldest son, RamВҰ187943, were Maats, YaminВҰ187947, and EkerВҰ187948.
\v 28 Onam'sВҰ187953 sons were Shammai and YadaВҰ187955, and Shammai'sВҰ187954 sons were Nadav and Avishur.
\p
\v 29 Avishur'sВҰ187963 wifeВҰ187962 was AvihayilВҰ187964, and \add вүҲtheir sons were\add* AhbanВҰ187969 and MolidВҰ187972.
\v 30 Nadav's sons were Seled andВҰ187974 Appayim. (Seled died childless.)
\v 31 Appayim's son was Yishi, Yishi's son was Sheshan, and Sheshan'sВҰ187989 son was AhlaiВҰ187992.
\p
\v 32 The sons of Shammai'sВҰ187997 brotherВҰ187996 YadaВҰ187995 were Yeter andВҰ187994 Yonatan. (Yeter died childless.)
\v 33 Yonatan's sons were PeletВҰ188008 and ZazaВҰ188009.
\m Those were the descendants of Yerahme'el.
\p
\v 34 SheshanВҰ188018 had no sonsВҰ188019, only daughtersВҰ188023. He had a \add male\add* servant from Egypt whose nameВҰ188027 was YarhaВҰ188028,
\v 35 and SheshanВҰ188031 gave his daughterВҰ188034 to \add *him\add* for a wife, and \add вүҲthey had a son\add* AttaiВҰ188042.
\v 36 Attai was the father of Natan, andВҰ188049 Natan was the father of Zavad.
\v 37 Zavad was the father of Eflal, andВҰ188060 Eflal was the father of Oved.
\v 38 Oved was the father of Yehu, andВҰ188071 Yehu was the father of AzaryahВҰ188075.
\v 39 Azaryah was the father of Helets, andВҰ188082 Helets was the father of EleasahВҰ188086.
\v 40 Eleasah was the father of Sismai, andВҰ188093 Sismai was the father of ShallumВҰ188097.
\v 41 ShallumВҰ188099 was the father of Yekamyah, andВҰ188104 Yekamyah was the father of Elishama.
\s1 The other descendants of Kalev
\rem /s1 Other Descendants of Caleb; Descendants of Hezron's Son Caleb
\rem /s2 The Clans of Caleb
\p
\v 42 The oldest son of Yerahme'el's brotherВҰ188112 Kalev was Meysha. Meysha was the father of Zif, andВҰ188110 Zif was the father of Mareshah. Mareshah was the father of Hevron.
\v 43 Hevron'sВҰ188126 sonsВҰ188125 were KorahВҰ188127, TappuahВҰ188128, RekemВҰ188129, andВҰ188125 ShemaВҰ188130.
\v 44 ShemaВҰ188132 was the father of Raham. Raham was the father of YorkeamВҰ188138. RekemВҰ188139 was the father of ShammaiВҰ188143.
\v 45 Shammai'sВҰ188147 son was Maon, andВҰ188149 Maon was the fatherВҰ188150 of Beyt-TsurВҰ188153.
\v 46 Kalev had a slave-wife named Eyfah who gave birth to Haran, MozaВҰ188164, andВҰ188155 Gazez. Haran had a son \add who he also named\add* Gazez.
\v 47 Yahdai'sВҰ188176 sonsВҰ188175 were: RegemВҰ188177, Yotam, GeshanВҰ188179, PeletВҰ188180, Eyfah, and ShaaphВҰ188182.
\p
\v 48 KalevВҰ188185 had \add another\add* slave-wife named MaacahВҰ188186 who gave birth to SheberВҰ188188 andВҰ188189 TirhanahВҰ188191.
\v 49 She also gave birthВҰ188193 to ShaaphВҰ188194 (the father of MadmannahВҰ188196), ShevaВҰ188199 (father of Makbenah and GibeaВҰ188203), and Kalev's daughterВҰ188204 Aksah.
\p
\v 50 These people were \add also\add* descendantsВҰ188212 of Kalev: \add His other wife\add* Efratah had a son Hur. Hur'sВҰ188216 sons were ShobalВҰ188219 (\add вүҲfounder\add* of KiriatВҰ188222-Yearim \add city\add*),
\rem /s1 Descendants of Caleb's Son Hur
\v 51 Salma (\add вүҲfounder\add* of Beyt-Lehem), \add and\add* HarefВҰ188229 (\add вүҲfounder\add* of Beyt-GaderВҰ188233).
\v 52 The descendants of ShobalВҰ188237 (\add вүҲfounder\add* of KiriatВҰ188240-Yearim) were HaroehВҰ188241, half of the Manahatites,
\v 53 and the clans from KiriatВҰ188248-Yearim: the Yitrites, the PutitesВҰ188250, the ShumatitesВҰ188251, and the MishraitesВҰ188252. From those cameВҰ188254 the Zoratites and EshtaolitesВҰ188256.
\v 54 Salma'sВҰ188260 descendants were \add the people of\add* Beyt-Lehem, the Netofatites, the clan of AtrotВҰ188264-Beyt-Yoav, and half of the Manahatites, \add who were also\add* ZoritesВҰ188269.
\v 55 The clans of the scribes lived at YabezВҰ188275: the TiratitesВҰ188276, the Shimeatites, andВҰ188271 the SucatitesВҰ188278. These are the Kenites who descended from HammatВҰ188282, the ancestor of Rekav's familyВҰ188271.
\c 3
\s1 King David's children
\rem /s1 Descendants of David; Descendants of David and Solomon; King David's Children
\rem /s2 The Sons of David
\p
\v 1 These were David'sВҰ188292 sonsВҰ188291 who were born to him in Hevron: the firstВҰ188299 was AmnonВҰ188301 by AhinoamВҰ188302 the Yezreelite, the secondВҰ188304 Daniyel by Avigayil the Karmelite,
\v 2 the thirdВҰ188309 Avishalom \add (AbsalomВҰ188310)\add*, the son of Maakah (daughterВҰ188314 of King TalmaiВҰ188316 of GeshurВҰ188318), the fourthВҰ188319 Adoniyyah, the son of HaggitВҰ188323,
\v 3 the fifthВҰ188325 Shefatyah by Avital, the sixthВҰ188328 Yitream by his wife EglahВҰ188330.
\m
\v 4 Six were born to \add @David\add* in Hevron \add вүҲwhere\add* he reigned for sevenВҰ188341 and a half years.\x + \xo 3:4: \xt 2Sam 5:4-5; 1Ki 2:11; 1Ch 29:27.\x*
\p Then he reigned in YerushalemВҰ188349 for thirty-three years
\v 5 and theseВҰ188352 were born to him \add *there\add*: Beyt-Shua (\add also known as Bathsheba,\add* daughterВҰ188365 of AmmielВҰ188367) gave birth to fourВҰ188361 \add sons\add*: ShimeaВҰ188357, Shovav, NatanВҰ188359, and Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ188360)\add*.\x + \xo 3:5: \xt 2Sam 11:3.\x*
\v 6 \add Other sons were\add* Yivhar, Elishama, ElifeletВҰ188371,
\v 7 NogahВҰ188373, NefegВҰ188374, YafiaВҰ188375,
\v 8 Elishama, Elyada, andВҰ188377 ElifeletВҰ188379. (Nine in all.)
\v 9 DavidВҰ188384 also had sons from his slave-wives. Their sisterВҰ188390 was TamarВҰ188389.
\s1 Descendants of King Shelomoh (Solomon)
\rem /s1 The Descendants of King Solomon; Descendants of Solomon
\rem /s2 The Kings of Judah
\p
\v 10 Shelomoh had a son Rehovoam, he had a son Aviyyah, he had a son AsaВҰ188399, he had a son YehoshafatВҰ188401,
\v 11 he had a son Yehoram, he had a son AhazyahВҰ188406, he had a son YoashВҰ188408,
\v 12 he had a son Amatsyah, he had a son AzaryahВҰ188413, he had a son YothamВҰ188415,
\v 13 he had a son Ahaz, he had a son Hizkiyah, he had a son Menashsheh,
\v 14 he had a son Amon, \add and\add* he had a son Yosiyyah.
\v 15 Yosiyyah had four sonsВҰ188430: The oldest was YohananВҰ188433, secondВҰ188434 was Yehoyakim, thirdВҰ188436 was Tsedekiyyah, \add andВҰ188430\add* the fourthВҰ188438 was ShallumВҰ188439.
\v 16 Yehoyakim had a son Yekaneyah, \add andВҰ188441\add* he had a son Tsedekiyyah.
\s1 Descendants of King Yekaneyah (Jeconiah)
\rem /s1 Descendants of Jehoiachin; The Descendants of King Jehoiachin
\rem /s2 The Royal Line After the Exile
\p
\v 17 Yekaneyah \add was captured andВҰ188448 taken to Babylon\add*. His sonsВҰ188448 were ShealtielВҰ188451,
\v 18 Malkiram, PedayahВҰ188455, Shenatstsar, YekamyahВҰ188457, HoshamaВҰ188458, andВҰ188454 Nedavyah.
\v 19 Pedayah'sВҰ188462 sons were Zerubbavel and ShimeiВҰ188464. \add Two of\add* Zerubbavel's sons were MeshullamВҰ188468 and HananyahВҰ188469, and theirВҰ188471 sisterВҰ188471 was ShelomotВҰ188470.
\v 20 Zerubbavel's fiveВҰ188479 \add other\add* sons were Hashubah, OhelВҰ188474, BerekyahВҰ188475, HasadyahВҰ188476, andВҰ188473 Yushab-HesedВҰ188478.
\v 21 Hananyah'sВҰ188483 descendants were PelatyahВҰ188484, YeshayahВҰ188485, \add and\add* the sons of Refayah, of ArnanВҰ188489, of Ovadyah, and of Shekanyah.
\v 22 Shekanyah's six descendants were Shemayah and Shemayah'sВҰ188498 sons HattushВҰ188501, Yigal, Bariyah, NearyahВҰ188504, and ShafatВҰ188505.
\v 23 Nearyah'sВҰ188510 threeВҰ188514 sonsВҰ188508 were Elyoenai, Hizkiyah, andВҰ188508 AzrikamВҰ188513.
\v 24 Elyoenai's sevenВҰ188526 sonsВҰ188516 were HodavyahВҰ188518, Eliashiv, PelayahВҰ188521, Akkuv, YohananВҰ188523, DelayahВҰ188524, andВҰ188516 AnaniВҰ188525.
\c 4
\s1 The other descendants of Yehudah (Judah)
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Judah; Descendants of Judah; Other Descendants of Judah
\rem /s2 Other Clans of Judah
\p
\v 1 Yehudah'sВҰ188530 sonsВҰ188529 were Perets, Hetsron, Karmi, HurВҰ188534, and Shoval.
\v 2 Shoval had a son Reayah, Reayah had a son Yahat, and Yahat had AhumaiВҰ188549 and LahadВҰ188552. Those were the ancestors of the Tsoratites.
\v 3 Yezreel, IshmaВҰ188562, and IdbashВҰ188563 \add вүҲstarted the clans that lived in\add* Eytam \add city\add*, and they had a sisterВҰ188565 named Hatselelponi.
\v 4 Hur was the firstВҰ188578 son born to \add his mother\add* Efratah, \add and\add* he \add вүҲfounded\add* Beyt-Lehem \add city\add*. Hur had theseВҰ188574 descendantsВҰ188575: Penuel and Ezer. Penuel \add вүҲstarted the clans that lived in\add* GedorВҰ188570 \add city\add*, and Ezer \add вүҲstarted the clans that lived in\add* HushahВҰ188573 \add city\add*.
\v 5 \add Hetsron's son\add* AshhurВҰ188584, the fatherВҰ188585 of TekoaВҰ188586, had twoВҰ188588 wivesВҰ188589, HelahВҰ188590 andВҰ188591 NaarahВҰ188591,
\v 6 and NaarahВҰ188595 bore him AhuzzamВҰ188598, HeferВҰ188601, Teymeni, and HaahashtariВҰ188607.
\v 7 \add Ashhur andВҰ188617 his wife\add* Helah'sВҰ188613 sonsВҰ188612 were TseretВҰ188614, Tsohar, EtnanВҰ188617,
\v 8 and Kots. Kots was the fatherВҰ188620 of AnubВҰ188623 and Hatstsovevah, and the ancestor of the clans descended from Harum'sВҰ188631 son AharhelВҰ188628.
\p
\v 9 Yabets was more respected than his brothersВҰ188636. His motherВҰ188637 had named him Yabets \add (which sounds like the word meaning вҖҳpainвҖҷ)\add*, saying, вҖңIt's because I bore him in pain.вҖқ
\v 10 Yabets calledВҰ188646 out to Yisrael's god, saying, вҖңOh, please give me a real blessing, and \add вүҲhelp me\add* and enlargeВҰ188655 my territory, and don't \add вүҲdo anything to harm me\add*, so that I won't be in pain.вҖқ And GodВҰ188648 \add вүҲdid what Yabets requested\add*.
\rem /s1 Other Family Lists
\p
\v 11 \add Another of Yehudah's descendants was\add* ShuhahВҰ188676. His brotherВҰ188674 Kelub was the father of Mehir. Mehir was the father of EshtonВҰ188683.
\v 12 Eshton was the fatherВҰ188697 of Beyt-RafaВҰ188690, PaseahВҰ188693, andВҰ188685 Tehinnah. Tehinnah \add ?вүҲfounded\add* NahashВҰ188699 city, but \add вүҲlived in\add* RekahВҰ188702.
\p
\v 13 Kenaz'sВҰ188706 sons were Otniel and SerayahВҰ188708. And Otniel's sons were HathathВҰ188711 \add ?and Meonotai\add*.\f + \fr 4:13 \ft Not in the Hebrew, but вҖҳsonsвҖҷ was plural, so it seems that it may have been accidentally dropped out of the text.\f*
\v 14 Meonotai had a son OfrahВҰ188717, andВҰ188718 SerayahВҰ188718 fatheredВҰ188723 Yoav, the \add вүҲfounder\add* of Craftsmen's Valley, because theyВҰ188728 were craftsmenВҰ188727.
\p
\v 15 The sons of Kalev (Yefunneh'sВҰ188735 son) were Iru, Elah, and NaamВҰ188738, and Elah'sВҰ188737 son was KenazВҰ188741.
\p
\v 16 Yehallelel'sВҰ188744 sonsВҰ188743 were ZifВҰ188745, ZifahВҰ188746, Tiriya, andВҰ188743 AsarelВҰ188748.
\p
\v 17 Ezrah'sВҰ188752 sonsВҰ188750 were YeterВҰ188753, Mered, EferВҰ188755, and YalonВҰ188756. And \add ?@Mered's wife Bityah\add* conceivedВҰ188757 Miryam, ShammaiВҰ188763, and IshbahВҰ188766, the fatherВҰ188767 of EshtemoaВҰ188768.
\v 18 \add *She\add* was one of Far-oh's \add (Pharaoh'sВҰ188793)\add* daughtersВҰ188791. Mered'sВҰ188796 wife, who was a descendant of Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*, gave birth to YeredВҰ188775 the father of GedorВҰ188777, Hever the father of Sokoh, andВҰ188770 Yekutiel the father of ZanoahВҰ188787.
\v 19 The sons of Hodiyyah's wife (Naham'sВҰ188803 sisterВҰ188802) were the father of KeilahВҰ188805 the GarmiteВҰ188806 and \add вүЎthe father of\add* EshtemoaВҰ188807 the Maakatite.
\p
\v 20 Shimon'sВҰ188811 sons were AmnonВҰ188812, RinnahВҰ188813, Ben-HananВҰ188816, and TilonВҰ188817.
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Shelah; Descendants of Judah's Son Shelah
\p Ishi'sВҰ188820 sons were Zohet and Ben-Zohet.
\s1 Shelah's descendants
\p
\v 21 The sons of ShelahВҰ188827 (one of Yehudah'sВҰ188830 sons) were ErВҰ188831 (father of Lekah), LaadahВҰ188834 (father of MareshahВҰ188836 and the clans \add вүҲwho worked with\add* linenВҰ188841 at Beyt-AshbeaВҰ188843),
\v 22 Yokim and the menВҰ188846 of KozebaВҰ188847, and YoashВҰ188848 and SarafВҰ188849, who ruledВҰ188852 in Moav and Yashubi-LehemВҰ188854. (\add вүҲAll this is from ancientВҰ188857 recordsВҰ188856\add*.)
\v 23 They were the pottersВҰ188860 \add вүҲwho lived in\add* NetaimВҰ188862 and GederahВҰ188863вҖ”theyВҰ188868 lived thereВҰ188869 and \add вүҲworked for\add* the kingВҰ188866.
\s1 The descendants of Shimeon (Simeon)
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Simeon; Descendants of Simeon; Simeon
\p
\v 24 Shimeon'sВҰ188873 sons were NemuelВҰ188874, YaminВҰ188875, YaribВҰ188876, ZerahВҰ188877, andВҰ188875 ShaulВҰ188878.
\v 25 Shaul's son was Shallum. Shallum's son was Mivsam. Mivsam's son was MishmaВҰ188884.
\v 26 The \add following were\add* Mishma's descendants: Mishma's son was Hammuel. Hammuel'sВҰ188889 son was Zakkur. Zakkur's son was ShimeiВҰ188893.
\v 27 Shimei had sixteen sons andВҰ188896 six daughtersВҰ188900, but none of his brothersВҰ188902 had many children, so Shimeon's \add вүҲdescendantsВҰ188912 were never as numerous as those\add* of \add his younger brother\add* YehudahВҰ188913 \add (Judah)\add*.
\p
\v 28 \add @Shimeon's descendants\add* livedВҰ188916 in \add these cities and towns\add*: Be'er-Sheva \add (Beersheba)\add*, MoladahВҰ188920, Hatsar-Shual,\x + \xo 4:28-33: \xt Josh 19:2-8.\x*
\v 29 Bilhah, Etsem, Tolad,
\v 30 Betuel, HormahВҰ188929, TsiklagВҰ188930,
\v 31 Beyt-Markaboth, Hatsar-Susim, Beyt-Biri, andВҰ188932 ShaaraimВҰ188938. \add вүҲThey lived in those places untilВҰ188941 DavidВҰ188944 became king\add*.
\v 32 They \add also\add* lived in fiveВҰ188953 villagesВҰ188946: Eytam, Ayin, RimmonВҰ188949, TokenВҰ188950, andВҰ188946 AshanВҰ188951,
\v 33 and all the villagesВҰ188957 aroundВҰ188959 theseВҰ188961 towns as far as BaalВҰ188964. Those were their settlementsВҰ188966, and theyВҰ188967 keptВҰ188967 their genealogicalВҰ188967 recordsВҰ188967.
\p
\v 34 \add Their clan leaders were\add* Meshovav, Yamlek, YoshahВҰ188972 the son of Amatsyah,
\v 35 Yoel, YehuВҰ188978 the son of YoshibiahВҰ188981, the son of SerayahВҰ188984, the son of AsielВҰ188987,
\v 36 as well as Elioenai, YaakobahВҰ188990, YeshohaiahВҰ188991, AsayahВҰ188992, AdielВҰ188993, YesimielВҰ188994, BenayahВҰ188995,
\v 37 and Ziza the son of ShifiВҰ189000, the son of AllonВҰ189003, the son of YedayahВҰ189006, the son of ShimriВҰ189009, the son of ShemayahВҰ189012.
\v 38 Those who are named above were the leadersВҰ189017 of their clans, and their \add extended\add* familiesВҰ189018 increased greatlyВҰ189022 in number,
\v 39 andВҰ189024 they wentВҰ189024 to the entranceВҰ189025 of GedorВҰ189026 (to the east of the valleyВҰ189029) in search of pastureВҰ189031 for theirВҰ189032 flocksВҰ189032.
\v 40 They foundВҰ189034 goodВҰ189037, \add вүҲfertileВҰ189036\add* pastureВҰ189035, and the land was \add вүҲwide\add*, and quietВҰ189041 and peacefulВҰ189042, because Ham'sВҰ189046 \add вүҲdescendants\add* had livedВҰ189047 thereВҰ189048 \add вүҲpreviously\add*.
\p
\v 41 Those listed by nameВҰ189054 wentВҰ189051 \add there\add* in the daysВҰ189055 of Yehudah'sВҰ189060 King HizkiyahВҰ189057 and struck down the tentsВҰ189064 of the MeunitesВҰ189067 who were foundВҰ189070 there. They completely annihilated them (to this dayВҰ189076), and they livedВҰ189078 \add there\add* in their placeВҰ189079 because there was pastureВҰ189082 for their flocksВҰ189083 there.
\v 42 ThenВҰ189086 fiveВҰ189096 hundredВҰ189097 of theirВҰ189104 menВҰ189095 who were descendantsВҰ189090 of Shimeon wentВҰ189092 to Mt. SeirВҰ189094, \add вүҲled\add* by Yishi's sonsВҰ189102 PelatyahВҰ189098, NearyahВҰ189099, Refayah, andВҰ189086 UzzielВҰ189101.
\v 43 They \add also\add* struck down the rest of the AmalekitesВҰ189111 who escapedВҰ189110, andВҰ189112 they've livedВҰ189112 thereВҰ189113 to this dayВҰ189115.
\c 5
\s1 Reuven's descendants
\rem /s1 Reuben; Descendants of Reuben; The Descendants of Reuben
\p
\v 1 Reuven was the first \add child\add* born to Yisrael \add (or IsraelВҰ189122, also known as Yakov/Jacob)\add*, but when he \add вүҲhad sex with one of his father'sВҰ189128 slave-wives\add*, his birthright was givenВҰ189129 to the sons of YosefВҰ189132 \add (Joseph)\add*, \add вүҲanother one of Yisrael's sons\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ189118 Reuven wasn't recorded as inheriting\add* the birthright,\x + \xo 5:1: \xt Gen 35:22; 49:3-4; Gen 49:8-10.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲand although\add* YehudahВҰ189141 \add (Judah)\add* was strongerВҰ189142 than his \add other\add* brothersВҰ189143 and \add вүҲwould be the son to produce a rulerВҰ189144\add*, the birthrightВҰ189146 went to Yosef.
\v 3 The sonsВҰ189150 of Yisrael's eldest son Reuven were Hanok, PalluВҰ189155, Hetsron, and Karmi.
\p
\v 4 \add Another of Reuven's descendantsВҰ189159 was\add* YoelВҰ189160, and his son was Shemayah. Shemayah'sВҰ189161 son was Gog. Gog'sВҰ189163 son was ShimeiВҰ189165.\x + \xo 5:6: \xt 2Ki 15:29.\x*
\v 5 Shimei's son was Mikah. Mikah's son was Reayah. Reayah'sВҰ189170 son was BaalВҰ189172.
\v 6 Baal's son was Beerah, who became a leaderВҰ189184 of the Reuvenites, \add but\add* the Assyrian King TiglatВҰ189179-Pileser \add вүҲcaptured him and tookВҰ189178 him back to AssyriaВҰ189182\add*.
\v 7 His brothers by their clans, \add вүҲas listed in their genealogicalВҰ189189 records\add*: YeielВҰ189192 the leader, Zekaryah,
\v 8 Bela son of AzazВҰ189198, son of ShemaВҰ189201, son of YoelВҰ189204. Reuven's clan lived near the city of AroerВҰ189207 \add as far north as the cities of\add* Nevo andВҰ189195 Baal-Meon.
\v 9 \add Some of them lived further\add* east, as far as the edge of the desert that extends to the EuphratesВҰ189224 River, because theirВҰ189226 livestockВҰ189226 had multiplied \add back\add* in the GileadВҰ189229 region.
\v 10 (In the daysВҰ189231 of \add King\add* ShaulВҰ189232, they'd battled with the HagritesВҰ189237 andВҰ189231 \add вүҲdefeated them, so thenВҰ189231\add* they'd livedВҰ189240 in their tentsВҰ189241 all over \add вүҲeasternВҰ189247\add* GileadВҰ189248.)
\s1 Gad's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Gad; The Descendants of Gad; Gad
\p
\v 11 Gad'sВҰ189253 descendants lived opposite them in the BashanВҰ189257 region as far as SalkahВҰ189260:
\v 12 Yoel was their leader, ShafamВҰ189264 was second-in-command, others were YanaiВҰ189266 and ShafatВҰ189267 in BashanВҰ189268.
\v 13 \add вүҲTheir cousins who were leaders of sevenВҰ189280 clans were\add* Mikael, MeshullamВҰ189274, Sheva, YoraiВҰ189276, Yakan, ZiaВҰ189278, andВҰ189270 EberВҰ189279.
\v 14 Those were descendants of Avihayil, the son of HuriВҰ189289, the son of YaroahВҰ189292, the son of GileadВҰ189295, the son of Mikael, the son of YeshishaiВҰ189301, the son of YahdoВҰ189304, the son of BuzВҰ189307.
\v 15 Ahi was the son of Avdiel, the son of GuniВҰ189315, head of theirВҰ189318 clans.
\v 16 \add @Those descendants of Gad\add* livedВҰ189320 in \add вүҲtownsВҰ189323\add* in the GileadВҰ189321 and BashanВҰ189322 regions, and on all the pasturelandВҰ189326 \add вүҲthroughout the SharonВҰ189327 Plain\add*.
\v 17 All of them were listed in the genealogies in the days of Yehudah'sВҰ189338 King YothamВҰ189335 and Yisrael's King YeroboamВҰ189340.
\s1 The eastern warriors
\rem /s1 The Tribes East of the Jordan; The Armies of the Eastern Tribes
\p
\v 18 There were 44,760 warriors descendedВҰ189346 from strong menВҰ189359 in the tribes of ReuvenВҰ189348 and Gad and the \add eastern\add* half of the tribe of MenashshehВҰ189353. They all carriedВҰ189360 shieldsВҰ189361 and swordsВҰ189362, and bows and arrows, and were all trained to fight in battles.
\v 19 They went to war against the HagritesВҰ189381, YeturВҰ189382, NafishВҰ189383, and Nodav,
\v 20 and were helpedВҰ189386 because they called out to God in the battleВҰ189396. \add вүҲSoВҰ189386\add* with God answeringВҰ189397 their prayersВҰ189397 because of their trustВҰ189401 in him, they \add вүҲwere able to defeat\add* the HagritesВҰ189390 and their \add вүҲallies\add*.
\v 21 They capturedВҰ189404 their livestockВҰ189405, including 50,000 camelsВҰ189406, 250,000 sheepВҰ189409, andВҰ189404 2,000 donkeysВҰ189413, as well as 100,000 people,
\v 22 because many were killed \add вүҲas a result of God's assistance\add*. Then they livedВҰ189428 in that \add вүҲarea\add* untilВҰ189430 the exileВҰ189432.
\s1 Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Half-Tribe of Manasseh; The People of East Manasseh
\p
\v 23 The descendants of the half tribeВҰ189437 of MenashshehВҰ189438 lived in the BashanВҰ189441 region as far as BaalВҰ189444-Hermon and SenirВҰ189446, and Mt. Hermon, \add and\add* they \add вүҲincreased in number\add*.
\v 24 Their clan leaders were EferВҰ189458, Yishi, ElielВҰ189460, AzrielВҰ189461, Yermiyah, HodavyahВҰ189463, and YahdielВҰ189464. They were all powerful and famous warriors, and leaders of their clans.
\s1 The exile of the eastern tribes
\rem /s1 The Eastern Tribes Are Deported
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ189474\add* they disobeyed theirВҰ189476 ancestors'ВҰ189476 god, andВҰ189474 they prostitutedВҰ189477 themselves to the godsВҰ189479 of the peoplesВҰ189480 that GodВҰ189475 had destroyedВҰ189485 \add вүҲahead of them\add* in that region.
\v 26 \add вүҲSoВҰ189489\add* Yisrael'sВҰ189491 godВҰ189490 stirredВҰ189489 up the spirit of the Assyrian King PulВҰ189496 (\add вүҲalso known as\add* TilgathВҰ189503-Pileser). He took them into exileвҖ”that is, the Reuvenites, the GaditesВҰ189509, and the half tribeВҰ189511 of MenashshehВҰ189512. ThenВҰ189489 he took them to HalahВҰ189514, HaborВҰ189515, HaraВҰ189516, and the riverВҰ189517 of GozanВҰ189518 (\add where they still are\add* toВҰ189519 this dayВҰ189520).\x + \xo 5:26: a \xt 2Ki 15:19; \xo b \xt 2Ki 15:29; \xo c \xt 2Ki 17:6.\x*
\c 6
\s1 Levi's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Levi; The Priestly Line; The Family Line of the High Priests; Levi
\p
\v 1 Levi'sВҰ189706 sonsВҰ189705 were GershonВҰ189707, KohatВҰ189708, andВҰ189709 MerariВҰ189709.
\p
\v 2 Kohat's sonsВҰ189714 were Amram, Yitshar, Hevron, and Uzziel.
\p
\v 3 Amram'sВҰ189723 children were Miryam \add (Miriam)\add*, Aharon \add (Aaron)\add*, and Mosheh \add (Moses)\add*.
\p Aharon's sonsВҰ189721 were Nadav, Avihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
\p
\v 4 Eleazar was the father of Pinehas, \add and\add* Pinehas was the father of Avishua.
\v 5 Avishua was the father of Bukki, and Bukki was the father of Uzzi.
\v 6 Uzzi was the father of Zerahyah, and Zerahyah was the father of Merayot.
\v 7 Merayot fathered Amaryah, and Amaryah fathered Ahituv.
\v 8 Ahituv was the father of Tsadok, and Tsadok was the father of Ahimaats.
\v 9 Ahimaats was the father of Azaryah, andВҰ189782 Azaryah was the father of Yohanan.
\v 10 Yohanan was the father of Azaryah. Azaryah was a priest in the temple that Shelomoh \add (Solomon)\add* built in Yerushalem.
\v 11 Azaryah was the father of Amaryah, andВҰ189798 Amaryah was the father of Ahituv.
\v 12 Ahituv was the father of Tsadok, and Tsadok was the father of Shallum.
\v 13 Shallum was the father of Hilkiyah, and Hilkiyah was the father of Azaryah.
\v 14 Azaryah was the father of Serayah, and Serayah was the father of Yehotsadak.
\p
\v 15 Yehotsadak \add вүҲwas included\add* when Yahweh \add вүҲsent\add* Nevuchadnetstsar to take Yehudah (\add вүҲwhich includes\add* Yerushalem) into exile.
\s1 Levi's other descendants
\rem /s1 Other Descendants of Levi; The Levite Clans
\p
\v 16 Levi's sons were Gershon, Kohat, andВҰ189838 Merari.\x + \xo 6:16-19: \xt Exo 6:16-19.\x*
\v 17 The names of Gershon's sons were Libni and Shimei.
\v 18 Kohat's sons were Amram, Yitshar, Hevron, and Uzziel.
\v 19 Merari's sons were Mahli and Mushi.
\p \add Here's a list of\add* \add вүҲLevi's descendants who became leaders of their clans:\add*
\p
\v 20 Gershon's \add oldest\add* son was Libni, Libni's son was Yahat, \add and\add* Yahat's son was Zimmah.
\v 21 Zimmah's son was Yoah, Yoah's son was Iddo, Iddo's son was Zerah, \add and\add* Zerah's son was Yeaterai.
\p
\v 22 \add Another line of Kohat's descendants started with his son Amminadav.\add* Amminadav's son was Korah. Korah'sВҰ189946 son was AssirВҰ189940.
\v 23 Assir's son was Elkanah. Elkanah's son was Evyasaf. Evyasaf's son was Assir.
\v 24 \add Assir's son was Tahat.\add* Tahat's son was Uriel. Uriel's son was Uzziyah. Uzziyah's son was Shaul.
\p
\v 25 Elkanah's sons were Amasai, Ahimot,
\v 26 and a son also named Elkanah. Elkanah's son was Tsofai. Tsofai's son was Nahat.
\v 27 \add Nahat's son was Eliav.\add* Eliav's son was Yeroham. Yeroham's son was Elkanah.
\p
\v 28 Shemuel had sons: his oldest son \add Yoel\add* and his other son Aviyah.
\p
\v 29 Merari'sВҰ190024 descendants started with Mahli. Mahli's son was Libni. Libni's son was Shimei. Shimei's son was Uzzah.
\v 30 \add Uzzah's son was Shimea.\add* Shimea's son was Haggiyah. Haggiyah's son was Asayah.
\s1 The temple musicians
\rem /s1 The Temple Musicians; Musicians Appointed by David
\rem /s2 The Temple Musicians
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 31 These \add are the men that\add* David put in charge of music in Yahweh's residence, after the \add sacred\add* chest was placed there.
\v 32 They were the ones who'd ministered in the sacred tent (\add also called\add* вҖҳthe meeting tentвҖҷ) with music until Shelomoh \add (Solomon)\add* built the temple in Yerushalem. They performed their duties according to their instructions.
\p
\v 33 \add вүҲHere's a list of the musicians\add* andВҰ190078 theirВҰ190078 sons:
\li1 From Kohat's descendants there was Heman, the leader of the singers.
\li1 Heman was Yoel's son.
\li1 Yoel was Shemuel's son.
\li1
\v 34 Shemuel was Elkanah's son.
\li1 Elkanah was Yeroham's son.
\li1 Yeroham was Eliel's son.
\li1 Eliel was Toah's son.
\li1
\v 35 Toah was Tsuf's son.
\li1 Tsuf was Elkanah's son.
\li1 Elkanah was Mahat's son.
\li1 Mahat was Amasai's son.
\li1
\v 36 Amasai was Elkanah's son.
\li1 Elkanah was Yoel's son.
\li1 Yoel was Azaryah's son.
\li1 Azaryah was Tsefanyah's son.
\li1
\v 37 Tsefanyah was Tahat's son.
\li1 Tahat was Assir's son.
\li1 Assir was Evyasaf's son.
\li1 Evyasaf was Korah's son.
\li1
\v 38 Korah was Yitshar's son.
\li1 Yitshar was Kohat's son.
\li1 Kohat was Levi's son.
\li1 Levi was the son of \add Yakov (or Jacob, who was later named\add* Yisrael/\add Israel)\add*.
\p
\v 39 Heman's cousin Asaf's \add group\add* stood to the right. Asaf was Berekyah's son. Berekyah was Shimea's son.
\v 40 Shimea was Mikael's son. Mikael was Baaseyah's son. Baaseyah was Malkiyah's son.
\v 41 Malkiyah was Etni's son. Etni was Zerah's son. Zerah was Adayah's son.
\v 42 Adayah was Etan's son. Etan was Zimmah's son. Zimmah was Shimei's son.
\v 43 Shimei was Yahat's son. Yahat was Gershon's son. Gershon was Levi's son.
\p
\v 44 Heman's cousin Merari's \add group\add* stood to the left. Eytan was Kishi's son. Kishi was Abdi's son. Abdi was Malluk's son.
\v 45 Malluk was Hashavyah's son. Hashavyah was Uzziah's son. Uzziah was Hilkiyah's son.
\v 46 Hilkiyah was Amtsi's son. Amtsi was Bani's son. Bani was Shemer's son.
\v 47 Shemer was Mahli's son. Mahli was Mushi's son. Mushi was Merari's son. Merari was Levi's son.
\p
\v 48 Their other Levite cousins were assigned to various ministries serving in God's residence in the sacred tent.
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Aaron; Aaron's Descendants
\v 49 \add вүҲIt was\add* Aharon \add (Aaron)\add* and his sons who \add вүҲwere responsible for offering\add* the sacrifices on the altar for burnt offerings and on the altar for incense, for all the work of the holiest place, and for making atonement for YisraelВҰ190333, according to everything that God's servant Mosheh \add (Moses)\add* had instructed.
\v 50 These were Aharon's descendants: Aharon's son was Eleazar. Eleazar's son was Pinehas. Pinehas's son was Avishua.
\v 51 Avishua's son was Bukki. Bukki's son was Uzzi. Uzzi's son was Zerahyah.
\v 52 Zerahyah's son was Merayot. Merayot's son was Amaryah. Amaryah's son was Ahituv.
\v 53 Ahituv's son was Tsadok, and Tsadok's son was Ahimaats.
\s1 The Levites' settlements
\rem /s1 Territory for the Levites; Where the Levites Lived; Settlements of the Levites
\p
\v 54 \add вүҲHere's a list of places where Aharon's descendants lived. Kohat's descendants were the first to be allotted property\add*.
\v 55 They were given \add the city of\add* Hevron in Yehudah \add (Judah)\add* and the surrounding pastureland,
\v 56 \add вүҲexcept that\add* Kalev \add (Caleb)\add* received the fields \add farther from\add* the city and the villages \add around\add* the city. (Kalev was Yefunneh's son.)
\v 57 Those descendants of Aharon were given Hevron (a refuge city), as well as these towns and their \add nearby\add* pastureland: Libnah, Yattir, Eshtemoa,
\v 58 Hilez, Devir,
\v 59 Ashan, and Beyt-Shemesh.
\v 60 From the Benyamin tribe, they received the cities of Geba, Alemet, and Anatot and their pasturelands. Altogether \add those Kohatite\add* clans received thirteen cities,
\v 61 and the remaining Kohatite clans received ten cities from the clans of the Menashsheh tribeВҰ190537.
\p
\v 62 The clans of Gershon's descendants received thirteen cities from the tribes of Yissakar \add (Issachar)\add*, Asher, Naftali, and the part of the Menashsheh tribe that lived in the Bashan region \add across the Yordan River\add*.
\v 63 The clans of Merari's descendants \add вүҲreceived\add* twelve cities from the tribesВҰ190585 of Reuven, Gad, and Zevulun.
\v 64 \add вүҲThe Israeli leaders allotted those\add* towns and the nearby pasturelands to the Levites.
\v 65 They also allotted them the cities from the tribesВҰ190616 of Yehudah, Shimeon, and Benyamin that were listed above.
\v 66 Some of Kohat's descendants received cities from the Efrayim tribe.
\v 67 They \add also\add* gave them these cities with the surrounding pasturelands: Shekem (a refuge city), Gezer,
\v 68 Yokmeam, Beyt-Horon,
\v 69 Ayyalon, and Gat-Rimmon.
\v 70 Kohat's other descendants received the cities of Aner and Bileam and the nearby pastureland from the half-tribe of Menashsheh \add (that lives west of the Yordan River)\add*.
\p
\v 71 Gershon's descendants also received, from the part of the Menashsheh tribe \add that lived across the Yordan River\add*, two cities and pastureland near them: Golan in the Bashan region, and Ashtarot.
\p
\v 72 From the Yissakar \add (Issachar) tribe they received these cities and\add* their nearby pastureland: Kedesh, Daverat,
\v 73 Ramot, and Anem.
\v 74 From the Asher tribe \add they received these cities and\add* their nearby pastureland: Mashal, Abdon,
\v 75 Hukok, and Rehob.
\p
\v 76 From the Naftali tribe \add they received these cities and\add* their nearby pastureland: Kedesh (in the Galilee region), Hammon, and Kiryatayim.
\p
\v 77 Merari's descendants \add received these cities and\add* their nearby pasturelands from the Zevulun tribe: Rimmono and Tabor.
\p
\v 78 From the Reuven tribe across the Yordan River (opposite Yereho), \add they were allotted these cities and towns and\add* and their nearby pastureland: Betser in the wilderness, Yahtsah,
\v 79 Kedemot, and Mefaat.
\p
\v 80 From the Gad tribe, \add they received these cities and\add* their nearby pastureland: Ramot in the Gilead region, Mahanayim,
\v 81 Heshbon, and Yazer.
\c 7
\s1 The descendants of Yissakar (Issachar)
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Issachar; Issachar; Descendants of Issachar
\p
\v 1 Yissakar'sВҰ190649 fourВҰ190655 sonsВҰ190648 were TolaВҰ190650, PuahВҰ190651, YashubВҰ190652, and ShimronВҰ190654.
\v 2 Tola's sonsВҰ190658 were UzziВҰ190660, Refayah, YerielВҰ190662, YahmaiВҰ190663, IbsamВҰ190664, and ShemuelВҰ190665 \add who all became\add* leaders of their clans. \add вүҲThere were strong warriors in the record of Tola's descendants in each generationВҰ190673\add*. (During the time that DavidВҰ190676 was Yisrael's king, there were 22,600 such men.)
\p
\v 3 Uzzi'sВҰ190686 son was Yizrahyah. Yizrahyah's five sons were Mikael, Ovadyah, YoelВҰ190692, and Yishiyah. They were all \add вүҲleaders of theirВҰ190696 clans\add*.
\v 4 Along with them according to their \add вүҲfamily records\add*, were 36,000 troopsВҰ190702 in the army, because theyВҰ190710 \add вүҲhad numerous\add* wivesВҰ190711 andВҰ190698 sonsВҰ190712.
\v 5 Altogether, Yissakar's clansВҰ190716 had 87,000 strong warriors listed in their genealogyВҰ190723.
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Benjamin; Benjamin; The Descendants of Benjamin and Dan
\p
\v 6 Benyamin'sВҰ190727 threeВҰ190731 \add sons\add* were BelaВҰ190728, BekerВҰ190729, and YediaelВҰ190730.
\v 7 Bela'sВҰ190734 fiveВҰ190740 sonsВҰ190733 were Etsbon, UzziВҰ190736, UzzielВҰ190737, Yerimot, andВҰ190733 IriВҰ190739 who were leaders of their clans. According to their family records, they had 22,034 strong warriors.
\p
\v 8 Beker's sons were ZemirahВҰ190756, YoashВҰ190757, EliezerВҰ190758, Elyehoenai, OmriВҰ190760, Yeremot, Aviyah, AnatotВҰ190763, and AlemetВҰ190764.
\v 9 Altogether, their clans had 20,200 strong warriors listed in their genealogyВҰ190772.
\p
\v 10 Yediael'sВҰ190785 son was Bilhan. Bilhan'sВҰ190786 sons were YeushВҰ190789, BenyaminВҰ190791, EhudВҰ190792, KenaanahВҰ190793, ZetanВҰ190794, TarshishВҰ190795, and AhishaharВҰ190796.
\v 11 All those descendants of YediaelВҰ190802 were \add вүҲclan leaders\add* and strong warriors, having 17,200 men ready to go to war.
\p
\v 12 The ShuppitesВҰ190816 and Huppites were descendants of Ir, \add and\add* the Hushites were descendants of AherВҰ190822.
\s1 The descendants of Naftali (Naphtali)
\rem /s1 Descendants of Naphtali; The Descendants of Naphtali; Naphtali
\p
\v 13 Naftali'sВҰ190825 sons were Yahtsiel, GuniВҰ190827, Yetser, and ShallumВҰ190829. (\add They were\add* descendants of \add Yakov's slave-wife\add* BilhahВҰ190831.)
\s1 Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Manasseh; Manasseh; Descendants of Manasseh
\p
\v 14 MenashshehВҰ190835 had sonsВҰ190834 by his \add вүҲSyrianВҰ190840\add* (Heb. ArameanВҰ190840) slave-wife. She gave birth to AsrielВҰ190836, and MakirВҰ190844 (\add who became\add* the fatherВҰ190845 of GileadВҰ190846).
\v 15 Makir \add вүҲmarried\add* a wife from the Huppites and ShuppitesВҰ190852. (His sister'sВҰ190854 name was Maakah.) \add вүҲAnother\add* descendant was Tselofehad and he had daughtersВҰ190861.
\v 16 Makir'sВҰ190867 wifeВҰ190865 (\add also calledВҰ190869\add* Maakah) bore a son and named him PereshВҰ190871 (and named his brother ShereshВҰ190874) and his sonsВҰ190875 were UlamВҰ190876 and Rakem.
\v 17 Ulam'sВҰ190880 son was BedanВҰ190881. Those were the descendantsВҰ190883 of GileadВҰ190884 (Makir'sВҰ190887 son andВҰ190879 Menashsheh'sВҰ190890 grandson).
\p
\v 18 \add @Gilead's\add* sisterВҰ190892 was HammoleketВҰ190893. She was the mother of IshhodВҰ190897, Aviezer, andВҰ190892 MahlahВҰ190903.
\p
\v 19 \add Another son of Gilead was\add* ShemidaВҰ190907, whose sonsВҰ190906 were Ahyan, Shekem, LikhiВҰ190910, andВҰ190905 AniamВҰ190911.
\s1 Efrayim's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Ephraim; The Descendants of Ephraim; Ephraim
\p
\v 20 These are Efrayim'sВҰ190915 descendants:
\p One son of Efrayim was Shutelah. Shutelah'sВҰ190916 son was Bered. Bered'sВҰ190917 son was Tahat. Tahat'sВҰ190919 son was Eleadah. Eleadah'sВҰ190921 son \add was also named\add* Tahat.
\v 21 \add @Tahat's\add* son was Zavad. Zavad's son was ShutelahВҰ190928. Efrayim's other sons, EzerВҰ190930 andВҰ190926 EleadВҰ190931, wentВҰ190939 to GatВҰ190935 city to steal some cattle but were killedВҰ190932 by \add вүҲsome of the natives of that area\add*.
\v 22 Their fatherВҰ190947 EfrayimВҰ190946 mournedВҰ190945 for \add вүҲquite some time\add*, andВҰ190950 his relativesВҰ190951 cameВҰ190950 to comfortВҰ190952 himВҰ190952.
\v 23 ThenВҰ190954 he \add вүҲslept with\add* his wife and she \add вүҲgot pregnantВҰ190958\add* and \add вүҲgaveВҰ190959 birthВҰ190959 to\add* a son. \add @Efrayim\add* \add вүҲnamed him\add* BeriahВҰ190965 \add (which sounds like the Hebrew word for вҖҳtroubleвҖҷ)\add*, because \add вүҲof the recent tragedy in their family\add*.
\p
\v 24 Efrayim's daughterВҰ190971 was Sheerah and she founded three towns: Lower Beyt-Horon, Upper Beyt-Horon, and UzzenВҰ190984-Sheerah.
\p
\v 25 \add Another son of Efrayim\add* was Refah. Refah's son was Reshef. Reshef'sВҰ190989 son was Telah. Telah'sВҰ190990 son was TahanВҰ190992.
\v 26 \add Tahan's\add* son was Ladan. Ladan's son was Ammihud. Ammihud'sВҰ190997 son was Elishama.
\v 27 \add Elishama's\add* son was Nun. Nun's son was Yehoshua \add (or Joshua, who led Yisrael's descendants after Mosheh)\add*.
\p
\v 28 \add This is a list of\add* \add вүҲthe cities and areas where Efrayim's descendants lived\add*: Beyt-El and the nearby villages, NaaranВҰ191014 to the east, GezerВҰ191016 to the west and the nearby villages, and Shekem and the nearby villages extending \add north\add* as far as AyyahВҰ191022 and its villages.
\p
\v 29 Along the border of the area where the descendants of MenashshehВҰ191030 lived were theseВҰ191041 towns: Beyt-Shan, Taanak, MegiddoВҰ191037, DorВҰ191039, andВҰ191025 all the nearby villages. The people who lived in all those places were descendants of Yakov's son YosefВҰ191044 \add (Joseph)\add*.
\s1 Asher's descendants
\rem /s1 Asher; The Descendants of Asher
\p
\v 30 Asher'sВҰ191051 sonsВҰ191050 were Yimnah, Yishvah, Yishvi, and BeriahВҰ191055. Their sisterВҰ191057 was SerahВҰ191056.
\p
\v 31 Beriah'sВҰ191060 sonsВҰ191059 were Hever andВҰ191062 Malkiel. Malkiel was the fatherВҰ191064 of Birzayit.
\p
\v 32 Heber was the fatherВҰ191069 of YafletВҰ191072, ShomerВҰ191075, HotamВҰ191078, andВҰ191068 theirВҰ191081 sisterВҰ191081 ShuaВҰ191080.
\v 33 Yaflet'sВҰ191084 sons were Pasak, BimhalВҰ191086, andВҰ191083 AshvatВҰ191087.
\p
\v 34 Shomer's sonsВҰ191092 were AhiВҰ191094, RohgahВҰ191095, Hubbah, andВҰ191092 AramВҰ191099.
\p
\v 35 \add Shomer's younger\add* brother was Helem. Helem'sВҰ191103 sonsВҰ191101 were Tsofah, Yimna, SheleshВҰ191107, andВҰ191101 AmalВҰ191108.
\p
\v 36 Zofah'sВҰ191111 sonsВҰ191110 were SuahВҰ191112, HarneferВҰ191113, ShualВҰ191114, BeriВҰ191115, YimrahВҰ191116,
\v 37 Betser, HodВҰ191119, ShammaВҰ191120, ShilshahВҰ191121, Yitran (whose other name was Yeter), and BeeraВҰ191123.
\p
\v 38 Yeter'sВҰ191126 sonsВҰ191125 were YefunnehВҰ191127, PispahВҰ191128, andВҰ191125 AraВҰ191129.
\v 39 \add Another descendant of Asher was\add* UllaВҰ191132, whose sonsВҰ191131 were ArahВҰ191133, HannielВҰ191134, andВҰ191131 Ritsia.
\p
\v 40 All those were Asher'sВҰ191142 descendantsВҰ191140, \add вүҲclan leaders\add*, chosenВҰ191147, very strong, \add вүҲleaders of leaders\add*. And listed in their genealogyВҰ191152 in the army for war, their numberВҰ191155, 26,000 men.
\c 8
\s1 Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Benjamin; The Genealogy of Saul the Benjamite; The Descendants of Benjamin
\p
\v 1 BenyaminВҰ191162 had sons: BelaВҰ191166, AshbelВҰ191168, AharahВҰ191170,
\v 2 Nohah, andВҰ191175 the fifthВҰ191176, RafaВҰ191175.
\p
\v 3 Bela'sВҰ191181 sonsВҰ191180 were AddarВҰ191182, GeraВҰ191183, AbihudВҰ191184,
\v 4 Avishua, NaamanВҰ191187, AhoahВҰ191188,
\v 5 Gera, Shefufan, andВҰ191190 HuramВҰ191192.
\p
\v 6 \add One of Gera's sonsВҰ191195 was\add* EhudВҰ191196. \add вүҲHis descendants were leaders of their clans who lived\add* in GebaВҰ191202 \add city\add*, but were taken into exile to ManahatВҰ191206.
\v 7 Ehud's sons were Naaman, AhijahВҰ191209, and Gera. Gera \add вүҲwas the one who led them\add* \add when they moved to Manahat\add*. He \add вүҲwas the fatherВҰ191213 of\add* Uzza and AhihudВҰ191219.
\p
\v 8 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was\add* ShaharayimВҰ191221 \add вүҲwho lived\add* in the MoabВҰ191224 countrysideВҰ191223. He \add вүҲdivorced\add* his wivesВҰ191233 HushimВҰ191229 andВҰ191230 BaaraВҰ191232
\v 9 andВҰ191235 fatheredВҰ191235 \add sons\add* with his wife HodeshВҰ191238: YobabВҰ191242, TsivyaВҰ191245, MeshaВҰ191248, MalkamВҰ191251,
\v 10 Yeuts, Sakeya, andВҰ191253 MirmahВҰ191261. They all became leaders of their clans.
\v 11 (He had fatheredВҰ191268 Avituv andВҰ191272 ElpaalВҰ191274 by Hushim.)
\p
\v 12 Elpaal'sВҰ191277 sonsВҰ191276 were EberВҰ191278, MishamВҰ191279, ShemedВҰ191280 (who builtВҰ191282 OnoВҰ191285 \add city\add*, plus LodВҰ191288 andВҰ191276 itsВҰ191289 townsВҰ191289),
\s2 Benyamin's descendants in Gat and Ayyalon
\rem /s1 The Benjaminites in Gath and Aijalon
\p
\v 13 plus Beriah andВҰ191292 ShemaВҰ191292 who were leaders of their clans who lived in Ayyalon \add city\add*. They forced the people who lived in GatВҰ191303 city to flee.
\v 14-16 Beriah's sons were Ahyo, ShashakВҰ191306, Yeremot, Zevadyah, Arad, Eder, Mikael, Yishpah, andВҰ191307 Yoha.
\s2 Benyamin's descendants in Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Benjaminites in Jerusalem
\p
\v 17-18 \add Other\add* descendants of Elpaal were Zevadyah, MeshullamВҰ191320, HizkiВҰ191321, HeberВҰ191322, Yishmerai, Yizliah, andВҰ191319 Yovav.
\p
\v 19-21 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was Shimei.\add* Shimei's descendants \add вүҲincluded\add* Yakim, ZikriВҰ191331, Zavdi, Elienai, Tsilletai, Eliel, Adayah, Berayah, andВҰ191330 Shimrat.
\p
\v 22-25 Shashak's sons were YishpanВҰ191344, EberВҰ191345, ElielВҰ191346, Avdon, Zikri, Hanan, Hananyah, Elam, Antotiyah, Iphdeiah, andВҰ191344 Penuel.
\p
\v 26-27 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was\add* Yeroham, whose sons were ShamsheraiВҰ191362, SheharyahВҰ191363, Atalyah, Yaareshyah, Eliyah, andВҰ191362 Zikri.
\p
\v 28 \add @All those descendants of Elpaal (Shaharayim's son)\add* were \add вүҲleaders of their clans accordingВҰ191375 to their genealogies\add*. They \add all\add* lived in YerushalemВҰ191379.
\s2 Benyamin's descendants in Gibeon
\rem /s1 The Family of Saul; The Benjaminites in Gibeon and Jerusalem
\p
\v 29 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was Yeiel\add*вҖ”he \add вүҲwas a founder of\add* GibeonВҰ191382 \add city\add*. His wife was Maakah.
\v 30 His sons, \add starting with\add* the eldest, were Avdon, TsurВҰ191393, KishВҰ191394, BaalВҰ191395, Nadav,
\v 31 Gedor, Ahyo, andВҰ191398 ZekerВҰ191400.
\v 32 Miklot \add (another of Yeiel's sons)\add* was the fatherВҰ191403 of Shimeah. All those descendants of Yeiel also lived in YerushalemВҰ191413 near their relativesВҰ191411.
\s1 The descendants of King Shaul (Saul)
\rem /s1 The Family of King Saul
\p
\v 33 NerВҰ191419 was the father of Kish. Kish was the father of \add King\add* Shaul. Shaul was the father of Yonatan \add (Jonathan)\add*, MalkiВҰ191436-ShuaВҰ191438, Avinadav, and Esh-Baal.
\v 34 Yonatan's son was Meriv-Baal. Meriv-Baal was the fatherВҰ191453 of Mikah.
\p
\v 35 Mikah'sВҰ191460 sonsВҰ191459 were PithonВҰ191461, MelekВҰ191462, TareaВҰ191463, and AhazВҰ191464.
\v 36 Ahaz was the father of Yehoaddah. Yehoaddah was the father of AlemetВҰ191475, AzmavetВҰ191478, andВҰ191466 Zimri. Zimri was the father of Motsa.
\v 37 Motsa was the fatherВҰ191489 of Binea. Rafah was Binea'sВҰ191492 son. Eleasah was Raphah's son. Atsel was Eleasah'sВҰ191495 son.
\p
\v 38 Atsel had \add вүҲa total of\add* six sons named AzrikamВҰ191505, Bokeru, YishmaelВҰ191508, ShearyahВҰ191509, Ovadyah, andВҰ191500 HananВҰ191511.
\v 39 Atsel had a brother, Eshek. Eshek'sВҰ191519 oldest son was UlamВҰ191521. His other sonsВҰ191518 were YeushВҰ191523 andВҰ191525 ElifeletВҰ191525.
\p
\v 40 Ulam'sВҰ191531 sons were powerful warriors who were also archers. Altogether they had 150 sons andВҰ191528 grandsons.
\p All those were Benyamin'sВҰ191548 descendants.
\c 9
\s1 Those who returned from captivity
\rem /s1 The restored community; The People Who Returned from Captivity
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* all Yisrael \add вүҲwere listed in genealogy\add*, and yes, they're writtenВҰ191556 on the scrollВҰ191559 of Yisrael's kingsВҰ191560.
\rem /s1 The Returning Exiles; The People in Jerusalem
\p Then Yehudah \add (Judah)\add* was takenВҰ191563 into exileВҰ191563 to BabylonВҰ191564 because of theirВҰ191565 unfaithfulnessВҰ191565.
\v 2 The firstВҰ191569 \add вүҲto return and resettle their land and\add* their cities were \add some\add* priestsВҰ191574, LevitesВҰ191575, templeВҰ191576 servantsВҰ191576, and \add other\add* Israelis.\x + \xo 9:2-3: \xt Ezr 2:27; Neh 7:73.\x*
\rem /s1 Inhabitants of Jerusalem after the Exile
\v 3 \add Some from the tribes of\add* YehudahВҰ191583, BenyaminВҰ191587, EfrayimВҰ191591, and MenashshehВҰ191592 \add also returned and\add* lived in Yerushalem, \add including the following:\add*
\p
\v 4 Utai son of Ammihud (Ammihud was Omri'sВҰ191600 son, Omri was Imri'sВҰ191603 son, Imri was Bani's son, Bani was a descendantВҰ191609 of Perets, Perets was Yehudah'sВҰ191614 son),
\v 5 Asayah andВҰ191621 his sonsВҰ191621 (descendants of ShilonвҖ”Asayah was the oldest),
\v 6 YeuelВҰ191628 andВҰ191623 other relativesВҰ191629 from Zerah'sВҰ191627 clan (which included 690 people).
\p
\v 7 From Benyamin' descendantsВҰ191637, SalluВҰ191639 (Meshullam'sВҰ191642 son, Meshullam was Hodavyah'sВҰ191645 son, Hodavyah was Hassenuah'sВҰ191648 son),
\v 8 Ibneyah (Yeroham'sВҰ191653 son), ElahВҰ191654 (Uzzi'sВҰ191657 son, Uzzi was Mikri'sВҰ191660 son), andВҰ191650 MeshullamВҰ191661 (Shefatyah's son, Shefatyah was Reuel'sВҰ191667 son, Reuel was Yivniyah's son).
\p
\v 9 In all, there were 956 of Benyamin's descendants living in Yerushalem. All those \add above\add* were leaders of their clans.
\rem /s1 The Returning Priests; Priestly Families; The Priests Who Lived in Jerusalem
\p
\v 10 Some of the priestsВҰ191690 \add who returned to Yehudah\add* were: YedayahВҰ191691, Yehoyariv, Yakin,
\v 11 Azaryah, the leading official at the temple (Azaryah was Hilkiyah's son, Hilkiyah was Meshullam'sВҰ191701 son, Meshullam was Tsadok'sВҰ191704 son, Tsadok was Merayot's son, Merayot was Ahituv's son),
\v 12 AdayahВҰ191716 (Yeroham'sВҰ191719 son, Yeroham was Pashhur'sВҰ191722 son, Pashhur was Malkiyah'sВҰ191725 son), and MaasaiВҰ191726 (Adiel'sВҰ191729 son, Adiel was Yahzerah'sВҰ191732 son, Yahzerah was Meshullam'sВҰ191735 son, Meshullam was Meshillemit'sВҰ191738 son, Meshillemit was Immer'sВҰ191741 son).
\p
\v 13 Altogether there were 1,760 \add priests who returned to Yehudah\add*. \add вүҲThey were leaders of their clans, and they all were capable and responsible\add* to workВҰ191754 in God's residence.
\s1 Levites who returned
\rem /s1 The Returning Levites; Levitical Families; The Levites Who Lived in Jerusalem
\p
\v 14 From Levi's descendants \add who returned to Yehudah there were\add*: ShemayahВҰ191762 (Hasshuv's son, Hasshuv was Azrikam'sВҰ191768 son, Azrikam was Hashavyah's son, Hashavyah was a descendant of \add Levi's youngest son\add* MerariВҰ191775),
\rem /s1 The Temple Guards Who Lived in Jerusalem
\v 15 Bakbakkar, HereshВҰ191778, GalalВҰ191779, MattanyahВҰ191780 (Mika's son, Mika was Zikri'sВҰ191786 son, Zikri was Asaf'sВҰ191789 son),
\v 16 Ovadyah (Shemayah'sВҰ191794 son, Shemayah was Galal'sВҰ191797 son, Galal was Yedutun's son), andВҰ191791 Berekyah who lived in one of the villagesВҰ191809 where the Netofat people lived (Berekyah was Asa'sВҰ191804 son, Asa was Elkanah'sВҰ191807 son).
\p
\v 17 From Levi's descendants who returned to Yehudah who guarded the temple gates there was Shallum, Akkuv, TalmonВҰ191815, AhimanВҰ191816, andВҰ191812 some of their relativesВҰ191817. Shallum was their leader.
\v 18 Those descendentsВҰ191830 of LeviВҰ191831 were gatekeepersВҰ191828 at the King's Gate on the east \add вүҲeven at the present time\add*.
\p
\v 19 Shallum was Kore'sВҰ191836 son, Kore was Evyasaph's son, and Evyasaph was Korah's son. Shallum and his relativesВҰ191843 from his clan (Korah's descendants), had the duty of being gatekeepers, responsible to guard the entrancesВҰ191860 to Yahweh's temple as theirВҰ191854 ancestorsВҰ191854 had done.
\v 20 \add вүҲPreviously\add* Pinehas (Eleazar'sВҰ191865 son) \add вүҲhad supervised\add* the gatekeepers. YahwehВҰ191870 was with \add @Pinehas\add*.
\p
\v 21 Zekaryah (Meshelemyah'sВҰ191876 son) was gatekeeperВҰ191877 of the entranceВҰ191878 to the assembly tent.
\v 22 \add вүҲAltogether, there were 212 men chosenВҰ191883 to guard the gates\add*. \add вүҲThe records of the clans in their villagesВҰ191890 listed their names\add*. \add King\add* DavidВҰ191894 and \add вүҲthe prophet\add* Shemuel \add (SamuelВҰ191895)\add* \add вүҲappointedВҰ191893 them because theyВҰ191889 were dependable\add*.
\v 23 They andВҰ191899 theirВҰ191900 sons \add watched\add* over the gatesВҰ191903 of Yahweh's house, i.e., the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent, as guardsВҰ191910.
\v 24 There were gatekeepersВҰ191915 on each of the \add temple's\add* fourВҰ191912 sidesВҰ191913: east, west, northВҰ191918, andВҰ191919 southВҰ191919.
\v 25 Their relativesВҰ191921 in their villagesВҰ191922 would come in from time to time \add to relieve them\add* for sevenВҰ191924 daysВҰ191925
\v 26 because the fourВҰ191937 leaders of the gatekeepersВҰ191939 were LevitesВҰ191941, and they were \add also\add* \add вүҲtrustedВҰ191935 to supervise\add* the chambersВҰ191945 and the treasuriesВҰ191947 in God'sВҰ191949 residence.
\v 27 TheyВҰ191954 would \add вүҲspend the nightВҰ191955\add* aroundВҰ191951 the \add вүҲtemple\add* while they were in charge, andВҰ191951 \add вүҲwould open it with the key each\add* morning.
\rem /s1 The Other Levites
\p
\v 28 Some of them \add вүҲmonitored the utensils used in the activities\add*вҖ”counting them as they broughtВҰ191975 them out andВҰ191976 \add вүҲwhen they put them away\add* \add again\add*.
\v 29 \add вүҲOthers\add* took care of the containers and utensils used in the sanctuaryВҰ191988, along with the fine flourВҰ191991, the wine and oil, and the frankincense and spicesВҰ191995.
\v 30 Some of the priestsВҰ192000 mixedВҰ192001 \add the fragrances andВҰ191997\add* spicesВҰ192003.
\p
\v 31 There was a LeviteВҰ192008 \add named\add* MattithiahВҰ192005 (the oldest son of ShallumВҰ192011, who was a descendant of Korah) whose official duty \add вүҲwas supervising the baking of the flat breads\add*.
\v 32 Some of Kohat's descendants preparedВҰ192029 the rows of breadВҰ192027 to \add laid out on the sacred table\add* every rest day.
\p
\v 33 Some of Levi's descendants were \add temple musicians and\add* singersВҰ192035. The leaders of those families stayed in the temple accommodations. They \add вүҲdidn't have other duties\add* because theyВҰ192046 \add were expected to\add* serve dayВҰ192044 and nightВҰ192045.
\v 34 Those were the headsВҰ192050 of the LeviteВҰ192052 \add вүҲfamiliesВҰ192051\add* accordingВҰ192053 to theirВҰ192053 generationsВҰ192053 \add and\add* theyВҰ192056 lived in YerushalemВҰ192057.
\s1 King Shaul's ancestors and descendants
\rem /s1 The Ancestors and Descendants of King Saul; The Genealogy of Saul; King Saul's Family Tree; The Family of King Saul
\r (1 Chr. 8:29-38)
\p
\v 35 \add Another descendant of Benyamin was\add* YeielВҰ192065. He was \add вүҲa founder\add* of GibeonВҰ192060 \add city\add* and lived there. His wife was Maakah.
\v 36 His oldest son was Avdon, andВҰ192071 his other sons were TsurВҰ192074, KishВҰ192075, BaalВҰ192076, NerВҰ192077, Nadav,
\v 37 Gedor, Ahyo, Zekaryah, andВҰ192080 MiklotВҰ192083.
\v 38 Miklot was the fatherВҰ192086 of Shimeam. They also lived \add вүҲnear\add* their relatives in YerushalemВҰ192096.
\p
\v 39 NerВҰ192102 was the father of Kish. Kish was the father of \add King\add* Shaul \add (SaulВҰ192111)\add*. Shaul was the father of Yonatan \add (Jonathan)\add*, MalkiВҰ192119-ShuaВҰ192121, Avinadav, and Esh-Baal.
\v 40 Yonatan's son was Meriv-Baal. Meriv-Baal was the fatherВҰ192137 of Mikah.
\v 41 Mikah'sВҰ192143 sonsВҰ192142 were PitonВҰ192144, MelekВҰ192145, andВҰ192142 TahreaВҰ192146.
\v 42 Ahaz was the father of Yarah. Yarah was the father of AlemetВҰ192157, AzmavetВҰ192160, andВҰ192148 Zimri. Zimri was the father of Motsa.
\v 43 Moza was the fatherВҰ192171 of Binea. Refayah was Binea'sВҰ192174 son. Eleasah was Refayah's son. Atsel was Eleasah'sВҰ192177 son.
\p
\v 44 Atsel had six sons named AzrikamВҰ192187, Bokeru, YishmaelВҰ192190, ShearyahВҰ192191, Ovadyah, andВҰ192182 HananВҰ192193.
\c 10
\s1 The death of King Shaul and his sons
\rem /s1 David succeeds Saul; Saul Takes His Life; Death of Saul and His Sons; The Death of King Saul
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Sam. 31:1-13)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* the Philistines foughtВҰ192200 against YisraelВҰ192201 and the IsraeliВҰ192205 men fled \add вүҲaway\add* from the Philistines, and \add вүҲmany were killed\add* on Mt. GilboaВҰ192211.
\v 2 ThenВҰ192213 the PhilistinesВҰ192214 pursuedВҰ192213 after ShaulВҰ192216 and after his sons, and \add *they\add* \add вүҲkilledВҰ192219\add* \add his\add* sons Yonatan, Avinadav, and Malki-ShuaВҰ192231.
\v 3 The battleВҰ192236 against ShaulВҰ192239 was very fierce, \add вүҲbut thenВҰ192235\add* the archers spotted him andВҰ192235 woundedВҰ192243 him.
\v 4 ThenВҰ192248 Shaul said to his equipment carrier, вҖңDraw your sword and pierce me with it, so those uncircumcisedВҰ192262 \add Philistines\add* \add ^can't come here\add* and torture me.вҖқ ButВҰ192248 his equipment carrier was very scared and wasn't willingВҰ192268 to do it, so Shaul took \add &his\add* sword and fell onto it.
\v 5 ThenВҰ192283 his equipment carrier, seeing that \add King\add* ShaulВҰ192289 had died, he himself fell on \add &his\add* sword andВҰ192283 died.
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* ShaulВҰ192301 and his threeВҰ192302 sonsВҰ192303 died, \add вүҲthus ending his family's rule\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ192314 all the IsraelisВҰ192313 living\add* in the valleyВҰ192317 sawВҰ192310 that \add @the army\add* had fled, and that ShaulВҰ192323 and his sonsВҰ192324 were dead, they abandonedВҰ192325 theirВҰ192326 citiesВҰ192326 and fled. ThenВҰ192310 the PhilistinesВҰ192329 cameВҰ192328, and they livedВҰ192330 in them \add instead\add*.
\p
\v 8 The next dayВҰ192335 \add вүҲwhen\add* the PhilistinesВҰ192337 cameВҰ192336 to stripВҰ192338 the deadВҰ192341, theyВҰ192336 foundВҰ192342 \add вүҲthe bodies of\add* ShaulВҰ192345 and his sonsВҰ192348 on Mt. GilboaВҰ192351.
\v 9 They strippedВҰ192353 himВҰ192353 and carried away his head and his armourВҰ192360. ThenВҰ192353 they sentВҰ192361 \add messengers\add* all aroundВҰ192366 the Philistine \add вүҲregions\add* to take the newsВҰ192367 to theirВҰ192370 idolsВҰ192370 and the peopleВҰ192373.
\v 10 They put his armourВҰ192378 in the \add вүҲtemple\add* of their godsВҰ192380, andВҰ192375 theyВҰ192384 hung his head in \add their god\add* Dagon'sВҰ192386 \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲWhen\add* everyone who lived \add back\add* in Yavesh in the GileadВҰ192392 region heardВҰ192389 about everything that the PhilistinesВҰ192399 had done to ShaulВҰ192400,
\v 12 all the strong men \add вүҲtookВҰ192407 action\add* and \add вүҲretrieved\add* the corpsesВҰ192410 of ShaulВҰ192411 and his sonsВҰ192414, and broughtВҰ192415 them \add back\add* to Yavesh. ThenВҰ192402 they buriedВҰ192417 \add вүҲthem\add* underВҰ192421 the large tree in Yavesh, and they fastedВҰ192424 sevenВҰ192425 daysВҰ192426.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ192428\add* ShaulВҰ192429 diedВҰ192428 because of his \add вүҲdisobedience\add*вҖ”when he was unfaithfulВҰ192430 to Yahweh \add вүҲby not following Yahweh's instructions\add*, andВҰ192428 also \add вүҲbecause he consultedВҰ192444 mediumВҰ192445\add* \add for guidance\add*\x + \xo 10:13: a \xt 1Sam 13:8-14; 15:1-24; \xo b \xt Lev 19:31; 20:6; 1Sam 28:7-8.\x*
\v 14 \add вүҲinstead of requesting Yahweh'sВҰ192451 advice\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ192448\add* \add @Yahweh\add* killed himВҰ192452 andВҰ192448 handed the kingdom over to Yishay'sВҰ192460 son DavidВҰ192457.
\c 11
\s1 David becomes king
\rem /s1 David Becomes King Over Israel; David Becomes King of All Israel; David Becomes King of Israel and Judah; David Anointed King of All Israel
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 5:1-10)
\p
\v 1 Then all YisraelВҰ192466 assembled around DavidВҰ192469 at Hevron, saying, вҖңLook, we're your fleshВҰ192474 and bone \add relatives\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲIn the recent past\add*, even when ShaulВҰ192485 was kingВҰ192486, \em you\em* were the one who took Yisrael out and the one who broughtВҰ192489 us back in. Plus your godВҰ192495 YahwehВҰ192494 told you, вҖҳYou yourself will shepherdВҰ192498 my people, Yisrael, and you yourself will become leader of my Israeli people.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ192512\add* all the IsraeliВҰ192515 eldersВҰ192515 wentВҰ192512 to the king at Hevron, andВҰ192512 David made a solemn agreement with them at Hevron \add вүҲin frontВҰ192526\add* of Yahweh. ThenВҰ192512 they anointedВҰ192528 David as king over YisraelВҰ192516 accordingВҰ192536 to Yahweh's messageВҰ192536 \add вүҲthat was given through\add* \add the prophet\add* Shemuel \add (SamuelВҰ192540)\add*.
\rem /s1 David Captures Jerusalem; David Conquers Jerusalem; Jerusalem Captured
\p
\v 4 Then DavidВҰ192544 and all YisraelВҰ192547 wentВҰ192543 to YerushalemВҰ192548 (\add Jerusalem, which was also known as\add* Yevus \add вүҲbecause the Yevusites were living thereВҰ192551\add*).\x + \xo 11:4: \xt Josh 15:63; Jdg 1:21.\x*
\v 5 The inhabitantsВҰ192557 \add вүҲinside\add* Yevus saidВҰ192556 to David, вҖңYou won'tВҰ192560 \add вүҲbe entering this place\add*.вҖқ ButВҰ192556 David capturedВҰ192563 \add what became known as\add* the TsiyyonВҰ192568 \add (ZionВҰ192568)\add* strongholdВҰ192567, that is, the cityВҰ192570 of David.
\v 6 \add *He\add* had saidВҰ192573, вҖңWhoever strikes down the Yevusites first will becomeВҰ192580 \add вүҲmy army commanderВҰ192581\add*.вҖқ Tseruyah's son Yoav went up \add over the wall\add* first, andВҰ192573 he became head \add of the army\add*.
\v 7 David \add started\add* living in that strongholdВҰ192594, so thenВҰ192592 they calledВҰ192598 it the cityВҰ192601 of David.
\v 8 He builtВҰ192604 the city up all aroundВҰ192606, from the terrace \add вүҲto the surroundingВҰ192612 walls\add*, andВҰ192604 Yoav restoredВҰ192614 the rest of the city.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ192620\add* DavidВҰ192621 \add вүҲbecame more powerfulВҰ192623 because\add* army commander YahwehВҰ192624 \add вүҲhelped\add* him.
\s1 David's powerful warriors
\rem /s1 David's Famous Soldiers; David's Mighty Men; David's Mighty Men and Their Exploits; David's Mightiest Men
\s4 Full kingdom
\rem /r (2 Samuel 23.8-39)
\p
\v 10 TheВҰ192647 following were the leaders of David'sВҰ192633 powerful warriors who together with all YisraelВҰ192641, strengthened his kingdomВҰ192636 andВҰ192629 established himВҰ192642 as kingВҰ192642, \add вүҲjust as\add* YahwehВҰ192644 had said.
\v 11 \add вүҲSo\add* theseВҰ192650 are David'sВҰ192654 powerfulВҰ192652 warriors: Yashaveam (a Hakmonite \add and\add* the leader of the thirty) once \add вүҲused\add* his spearВҰ192667 against three hundredВҰ192672 men in a single battle and killed them all.
\v 12 Next was EleazarВҰ192678 (an AhohiteВҰ192682, son of DodoВҰ192681) who was one of the \add top\add* threeВҰ192684 powerfulВҰ192685 warriors.
\v 13 He was with DavidВҰ192692 at Pas-Dammim \add вүҲwhen\add* the Philistines had assembled thereВҰ192698 for battleВҰ192700 \add вүҲnear\add* a part of the countrysideВҰ192703 \add вүҲwhere barleyВҰ192705 was growing\add*. \add вүҲAt first, the Israelis\add* fled from the Philistines,
\v 14 \add вүҲbut thenВҰ192711\add* they tookВҰ192711 their standВҰ192711 in the middleВҰ192712 of the \add вүҲbarley\add* andВҰ192711 \add вүҲproceeded to defeat\add* the PhilistinesВҰ192719 \add вүҲas\add* YahwehВҰ192721 savedВҰ192720 them through a stunning victoryВҰ192722.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ192725 threeВҰ192726 of that top thirtyВҰ192729 wentВҰ192725 down to DavidВҰ192736, near the rockВҰ192733 at Adullam'sВҰ192740 cave. \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* PhilistinesВҰ192742 had encampedВҰ192743 in the RefaimВҰ192745 Valley.
\v 16 David was in that strongholdВҰ192749 thenВҰ192747, andВҰ192750 the Philistine garrisonВҰ192750 was in Beyt-Lehem
\v 17 and DavidВҰ192758 \add вүҲwas thirsty and asked\add*, вҖңWho'll get me waterВҰ192762 to drinkВҰ192761 from the well by the Beyt-Lehem gateВҰ192768?вҖқ
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ192770 those\add* threeВҰ192771 brokeВҰ192770 through the Philistine camp, and they drew waterВҰ192776 from the well at the Beyt-Lehem gateВҰ192782, and they broughtВҰ192784 it back to David. \add вүҲButВҰ192770\add* David wasn't willingВҰ192790 to drinkВҰ192792 it, and he pouredВҰ192793 it out \add on the ground as an offering\add* to YahwehВҰ192795.
\v 19 вҖңFar be it from me beforeВҰ192800 my godВҰ192800 \add вүҲto drink this water\add*,вҖқ he said. вҖңCould I drink the bloodВҰ192803 of these menВҰ192804 \add вүҲwho risked\add* their lives to bring it?вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ192797\add* he wasn't \add вүҲprepared\add* to drink it. Those were \add some of the things\add* that those threeВҰ192816 powerful warriors did.
\rem /s1 David's Thirty Mighty Men
\p
\v 20 Yoav's brotherВҰ192820 Abshai, was the head of a group of three. He had killed three hundredВҰ192836 with is spearВҰ192832 and had a reputation among the three.\f + \fr 11:20 \ft This seems unexpectedly similar to verse 11 and might possibly indicate some confusion in the early records.\f*
\v 21 He was honouredВҰ192848 more than the other two and became the leader of that \add ?second\add* group of three, \add вүҲbut\add* didn'tВҰ192855 enter the \add ?first\add* Three.
\p
\v 22 Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ192860 from Kavtse'el was a powerful warriorВҰ192879 who did amazing things. He struckВҰ192876 down Ariel's twoВҰ192878 \add sons\add* from MoabВҰ192880. \add вүҲAnother time,\add* he climbed down into a pit on a snowyВҰ192890 dayВҰ192889 and killedВҰ192883 the lionВҰ192886 \add вүҲthat was trapped\add* in the pit.
\v 23 He \add also\add* \add вүҲkilled\add* a \add вүҲhuge\add* Egyptian manвҖ”well over 2m tall. The Egyptian \add вүҲwas carrying\add* a spear like a weaver'sВҰ192908 beam, but \add @Benayah\add* went down to \add take him on\add* with a staff. He forced the spear from the Egyptian's \add вүҲgrasp\add*, andВҰ192892 thenВҰ192892 killed him with \add *it\add*.
\v 24 \add So\add* that was what BenayahВҰ192923 (Yehoyada's son) did \add вүҲthat gave him a reputation\add* among the threeВҰ192930 powerfulВҰ192931 warriors.
\v 25 \add Actually,\add* he was honouredВҰ192937 more than the Thirty, \add вүҲyet\add* he didn'tВҰ192942 \add вүҲmake it to\add* the \add first\add* Three, \add вүҲbut\add* DavidВҰ192946 \add вүҲappointed\add* him over his bodyguardsВҰ192949.
\p
\v 26 These are the names of the powerful warriors: Asahel (Yoav's brotherВҰ192957), ElhananВҰ192959 (Dodo'sВҰ192962 son from Beyt-Lehem),
\v 27 ShammotВҰ192967 (from Haror), Helets (from Pelon),
\v 28 IraВҰ192973 (Ikkesh'sВҰ192976 son from TekoaВҰ192977), AviezerВҰ192978 (from AnatotВҰ192979),
\v 29 Sibbekai (from Hushah), IlaiВҰ192984 (from Ahoh),
\v 30 MaharaiВҰ192988 (from Netofah), HeledВҰ192990 (Baanah'sВҰ192993 son from Netofah),
\v 31 ItaiВҰ192997 (Rivai's son from Giveah which belonged to Benyamin'sВҰ193003 descendantsВҰ193002), BenayahВҰ193005 (from Piraton),
\v 32 Hurai (from the valleys near Mt. GaashВҰ193010), Aviel (from Aravah),
\v 33 AzmavetВҰ193016 (from Baharum), Elyahba (from Shaalvon),
\v 34 Hashem'sВҰ193023 sonsВҰ193022 (from Gizon), Yonatan (Shagee'sВҰ193028 son from Harar),
\v 35 AhiamВҰ193032 (Sakar'sВҰ193035 son from HararВҰ193036), ElifalВҰ193037 (Ur'sВҰ193040 son),
\v 36 HeferВҰ193043 (from Mekerat), Ahiyyah (from Pelon),
\v 37 HezroВҰ193049 (from KarmelВҰ193050), NaaraiВҰ193051 (Ezbai'sВҰ193054 son),
\v 38 YoelВҰ193057 (Natan'sВҰ193059 brotherВҰ193058), MivharВҰ193060 (Hagri'sВҰ193063 son),
\v 39 TselekВҰ193066 (the AmmoniteВҰ193067), NaharaiВҰ193068 (from BeerotВҰ193069, armourВҰ193071 bearerВҰ193070 for Tseruyah's son Yoav),
\v 40 IraВҰ193078 (the Yitrite), Garev (the Yitrite),
\v 41 Uryyah (Bat-Sheba's husband the HittiteВҰ193085), Zavad (Ahlai'sВҰ193089 son),
\v 42 AdinaВҰ193092 (Shiza'sВҰ193095 son from the tribe of Reuven, a leader from that tribe who had thirtyВҰ193100 soldiers with himВҰ193099),
\v 43 HananВҰ193103 (Maakah's son), YoshafatВҰ193107 (from Mithna),
\v 44 Uzziyya (from Ashterat), ShamaВҰ193113 andВҰ193114 YeielВҰ193114 (Hotam'sВҰ193118 sonsВҰ193117 from Aroer),
\v 45 YediaelВҰ193122 (Shimri'sВҰ193125 son) andВҰ193126 his brother YohaВҰ193126 (from TizВҰ193128),
\v 46 ElielВҰ193131 (from Mahavah), Yerivai and YoshaviahВҰ193134 (Elnaam'sВҰ193136 sonsВҰ193135), Yitmah (from Moav),
\v 47 Eliel and ObedВҰ193141, and YaasielВҰ193142 (from Zobah).
\c 12
\s1 The heroes accompanied to David
\rem /s1 David's Followers in the Wilderness; Warriors Join David's Army; David's Early Followers from the Tribe of Benjamin; Warriors Join David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 These were the men who joined David in TsiklagВҰ193151, when he was \add вүҲbanished\add* from Kish'sВҰ193158 son, Shaul'sВҰ193155 presence. (They were among the warriorsВҰ193160 who assisted \add @David\add* in battle
\v 2 armed with bows. \add Some\add* \add вүҲused slings\add* right-handed and \add some\add* left-handed as well as \add вүҲshooting\add* arrowsВҰ193169 with a bow. \add They were\add* from \add the tribe of\add* BenyaminВҰ193173, Shaul'sВҰ193172 relatives.)
\v 3 Their leader was AhiezerВҰ193176, then next was YoashВҰ193177, both Shemaah'sВҰ193179 sons from Gibeah \add city\add*. \add Others were:\add* YezielВҰ193181 and PeletВҰ193183 (Azmavet'sВҰ193185 sons), Berakah, YehuВҰ193187 (from AnatotВҰ193188 \add city\add*),
\rem /s1 David's Followers from the Tribe of Gad
\v 4 YishmayahВҰ193190 (from Gibeon \add city\add*, who was the leader of the thirty greatest warriors), Yeremyah, Yahaziel, Yohanan, Yozabad (from Gederah \add city\add*),
\v 5 Eluzai, Yerimot, Bealyah, Shemaryah, Shefatyah (from Haruf \add city\add*),
\v 6 Elkanah, Yishshiyah, Azarel, Yoezer, and Yashoveam (all Korah's descendants),
\v 7 and Yoelah and Zevadyah (Yeroham's sons, from Gedor \add city\add*).
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSome\add* Gadites \add вүҲjoined\add* David at the wilderness stronghold. \add They were\add* very strong army warriors, ready for battle with shields and spears. \add вүҲTheir faces were fierce like lions, but they could run across the hills like\add* gazelles.
\v 9 Their leader was Ezer, then Ovadyah, then Eliav.
\v 10 Next was Mishmannah, then Yermeyah,
\v 11 Attai, Eliel,
\v 12 Yohanan, Elzavad,
\v 13 \add another\add* Yermeyah, then the eleventh was Makbannai.
\p
\v 14 Those men from the \add вүҲtribe\add* of Gad were army leadersвҖ”\add вүҲeach leading somewhere between\add* one hundred and one thousand \add men\add*.
\v 15 They crossed to the west side of the Yordan \add River\add* \add вүҲduring the spring, at the time of the year when the river floods\add*. They \add вүҲdrove out all the people who lived in the valleys on both sides\add* \add of the river\add*.
\rem /s1 Followers from Benjamin and Judah
\p
\v 16 \add Some other men\add* \add вүҲfrom the tribes\add* of Benyamin and Yehudah also went to David in his stronghold.
\v 17 DavidВҰ193344 wentВҰ193335 out \add of the cave\add* \add вүҲto meet them\add*, and he told them: вҖңIf you've come to me in peace, to help me, \add вүҲthen I'll be happy to agree with\add* you all. \add вүҲBut\add* if \add you all plan\add* to betray me to my enemies \add вүҲeven though I've done you all no harm\add*, may the god of our ancestors see \add your motives\add* and judge.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 Then \add the\add* spirit \add вүҲempowered\add* Amasai, the head of the thirty, \add and he said\add*: вҖңTo you, David, and with you, son of Yishay \add (Jesse)\add*. Peace, peace to you and peace to the one who helps you, because your godВҰ193373 has helped you.вҖқ And David received them and placed them as the heads of the troop.
\rem /s1 Followers from Manasseh
\p
\v 19 \add Some men\add* from Menashsheh \add вүҲjoined\add* David when he \add вүҲaccompanied\add* the Philistines to battle against \add King\add* Shaul. (\add вүҲBut\add* \add @David and his men\add* didn't help \add @the Philistines\add* because the Philistines' governors \add вүҲwere advised\add* to send them away \add вүҲas there was a worry that David would feel loyal to his former master, and hence turn on them\add*.)
\v 20 As \add @David\add* was going to Tsiklag, \add вүҲthe following men from Menashsheh joined\add* himВҰ193427: Adnah, Yozavad, Yediael, Mikael, \add another\add* Yozavad, Elihu, and TsilletaiвҖ”the \add вүҲcaptains\add* of \add units of\add* thousands from Menashsheh.
\v 21 They helped David \add stand\add* against \add вүҲbands of raiders\add*, because all of them \add вүҲwere powerful warriors and military leaders\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲEvery day more men joined\add* to help DavidВҰ193464, until his army became very large \add вүҲlike the Israeli people themselves\add*.
\rem /s1 Others Join David at Hebron; David's Army at Hebron; List of David's Forces
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲThe following are\add* the numbers of the leaders of those equipped for war. They cameВҰ193483 to DavidВҰ193486 at Hevron to \add вүҲhelpВҰ193487 himВҰ193487 obtain Shaul's kingdom as Yahweh had promised\add*.
\li1
\v 24 From Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*: 6,800 \add warriors\add* ready for battle with shields andВҰ193497 spears.
\li1
\v 25 From Shimeon \add (Simeon)\add*: 7,100 powerful \add warriors\add* ready for battle.
\li1
\v 26 From Levi: 4,600.
\li1
\v 27 Yehoyada (a leader \add descendedВҰ193545\add* from Aharon) brought 3,700 with him.
\li1
\v 28 Tsadok, a strong young man \add brought\add* twenty-two leadersВҰ193555 \add вүҲfrom his clan\add*.
\li1
\v 29 From Benyamin (Shaul's tribe): 3,000 (\add вүҲmost of whom had previously served\add* \add King\add* Shaul).
\li1
\v 30 From Efrayim: 20,800 \add вүҲpowerful warriors who were admired within theirВҰ193589 own clans\add*
\li1
\v 31 From the half-tribe of Menashsheh: 18,000 who were \add вүҲknown by name\add* came to make David king.
\li1
\v 32 From Yissakar: 200 leaders (\add вүҲwith a good understanding of the times and the right thing to do\add*) along with their relatives that theyВҰ193621 commanded.
\li1
\v 33 From Zevulun: 50,000 \add вүҲexperienced warriors with each kind of weapon\add* and \add ?вүҲstoic in attitude yet loyal\add*.
\li1
\v 34 From Naftali: 1,000 officers, along with 37,000 \add men\add* carrying shields and spears.
\li1
\v 35 From Dan: 28,600 \add men\add* prepared for battle.
\li1
\v 36 From Asher: 40,000 \add warriors\add* preparedВҰ193686 for battleВҰ193687.
\li1
\v 37 From Reuven, Gad, and the Menashsheh half-tribe across the Yordan \add river\add*: 120,000 \add men\add* armed with all kinds of weapons.
\p
\v 38 All those \add вүҲenthusiastic and capable warriors\add* came to Hevron to make David king over all Yisrael. The rest of Yisrael was also \add вүҲunited in wanting\add* to make David king.
\v 39 They were there with DavidВҰ193740 three days, eating andВҰ193746 drinking, \add вүҲbecause their families had sent provisions with them\add*.
\v 40 Also, those \add вүҲwho lived near that area\add* (\add even\add* as far as Yissakar and Zevulun and Naftali) were bringing bread on donkeys and camels, and on mules and on oxen: plentiful supplies of flour, fig cakes, raisin cakes, wine, and oil, as well as oxen and sheep, because Yisrael \add вүҲwas celebrating\add*.
\c 13
\s1 Moving the box containing the agreement
\rem /s1 David Attempts to Move the Ark; The Ark Brought from Kiriath-jearim; The Covenant Box Is Moved from Kiriath Jearim; Bringing Back the Ark
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 6:1-11)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day\add* DavidВҰ193808 consultedВҰ193807 with all his leadersВҰ193816вҖ”the commandersВҰ193811 of thousandsВҰ193812 and of hundredsВҰ193813.
\v 2 DavidВҰ193819 saidВҰ193818 to all the assemblyВҰ193822 of YisraelВҰ193823, вҖңIfВҰ193840 it \add sounds\add* goodВҰ193827 to youВҰ193826 all, and to our godВҰ193831 YahwehВҰ193830, let's spreadВҰ193832 out to \add вүҲall our different regions to recruit\add* our relatives, along with the priestsВҰ193842 and the LevitesВҰ193843 in the citiesВҰ193844 of theirВҰ193845 pasturelandsВҰ193845, \add вүҲso they can join\add* us.
\v 3 And let's return ourВҰ193853 god's boxВҰ193852 \add вүҲback here\add*, because we didn'tВҰ193857 \add вүҲuse itВҰ193858 to ask GodВҰ193853 for guidance in Shaul'sВҰ193860 time\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 All the assembledВҰ193865 peopleВҰ193875 agreed because everyoneВҰ193875 \add вүҲcould see that itВҰ193870 was the right thingВҰ193871 to do\add*.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ193877\add* DavidВҰ193878 assembledВҰ193877 all YisraelВҰ193883 from ShihorВҰ193886 \add river down\add* in EgyptВҰ193887 andВҰ193888 as far \add north\add* as LeboВҰ193890-HamatВҰ193891, to bringВҰ193892 in God's chestВҰ193895 from Kiriat-Yearim.\x + \xo 13:5: \xt 1Sam 7:1-2.\x*
\v 6 ThenВҰ193900 DavidВҰ193901 andВҰ193902 all YisraelВҰ193904 went to KiriatВҰ193908-YearimВҰ193909 (\add also known as\add* BaalahВҰ193905, in YehudahВҰ193911), to bringВҰ193912 up from thereВҰ193913 the box of God YahwehВҰ193918 who sitsВҰ193919 over the winged creatures. \add The box is used when\add* \add вүҲcallingВҰ193923 his nameВҰ193924\add* \add to request help\add*.\x + \xo 13:6: \xt Exo 25:22.\x*
\v 7 They transported God's boxВҰ193929 on a new cart from Avinadav's houseВҰ193935, and UzzahВҰ193937 and Ahyo were leadingВҰ193939 the cart
\v 8 and David and all YisraelВҰ193945 were celebrating \add вүҲin frontВҰ193947\add* of God with all \add вүҲtheir energy\add*, and with songsВҰ193952, and with lyresВҰ193953, harpsВҰ193954, tambourinesВҰ193955, cymbalsВҰ193956, and trumpetsВҰ193957.
\p
\v 9 \add However\add* \add вүҲjust as they were passing\add* Kidon'sВҰ193963 threshingВҰ193962 floorВҰ193962, the oxen stumbledВҰ193974 andВҰ193959 UzzahВҰ193965 \add вүҲreached out to steady\add* the boxВҰ193972.
\v 10 \add That made\add* YahwehВҰ193980 \add вүҲvery angry with\add* UzzahВҰ193981, and he struckВҰ193982 him down because he \add вүҲhad reached out to touch\add* the boxВҰ193990, and he diedВҰ193991 \add right\add* thereВҰ193992 \add вүҲin frontВҰ193993\add* of GodВҰ193994.
\v 11 \add That in turn made\add* DavidВҰ193997 angry because YahwehВҰ194001 \add вүҲhad burst out\add* against Uzzah, andВҰ193996 he named that placeВҰ194005 Perets-Uzzah \add (which means вҖҳoutburst against UzzahвҖҷ)\add* untilВҰ194009 this dayВҰ194010.
\p
\v 12 DavidВҰ194014 \add вүҲwas afraidВҰ194013 of\add* God that dayВҰ194018 \add вүҲandВҰ194013 asked himself\add*, вҖңHow can I possible bringВҰ194022 God's boxВҰ194025 to where I am \add in Yerushalem\add*?вҖқ
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ194028\add* David \add вүҲgave up on bringing the boxВҰ194034 to where he was\add* in the cityВҰ194038 of David, andВҰ194028 \add instead\add* he tookВҰ194040 it into the \add nearby\add* houseВҰ194043 of Oved-EdomВҰ194046 the GittiteВҰ194047.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ194049\add* God's boxВҰ194050 stayed at Oved-Edom's houseВҰ194057 for threeВҰ194058 monthsВҰ194059, and YahwehВҰ194061 blessedВҰ194060 Oved-Edom's home and everything that belonged to him.\x + \xo 13:14: \xt 1Ch 26:4-5.\x*
\c 14
\s1 David вҖҳexpansionвҖҷ in Yerushalem
\rem /s1 David's Palace and Family; David Established at Jerusalem; David's House and Family; David's Activities in Jerusalem
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 2:11-16)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day\add* King Hiram from Tsor \add (TyreВҰ194082)\add* sentВҰ194077 messengersВҰ194083 to DavidВҰ194086, along with cedarВҰ194088 timber and \add вүҲstoneВҰ194089 masons and carpenters\add* to buildВҰ194093 a houseВҰ194095 for him.
\v 2 \add By thenВҰ194097\add* DavidВҰ194098 \add вүҲhad realised\add* that Yahweh had establishedВҰ194101 himВҰ194101 as kingВҰ194103 over YisraelвҖ”that his kingdomВҰ194111 was \add вүҲbeing made more prominent\add* for the sake of \add @Yahweh's\add* peopleВҰ194113 Yisrael.
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ194123 DavidВҰ194118 tookВҰ194117 more wivesВҰ194120 in YerushalemВҰ194121 and \add *he\add* fatheredВҰ194122 more sonsВҰ194125 and daughtersВҰ194126.
\v 4 These \add вүҲare his children\add* who were born \add there\add* in YerushalemВҰ194135: ShammuaВҰ194136, Shovav, NatanВҰ194138, Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ194139)\add*,
\v 5 Ibhar, ElishuaВҰ194142, ElpeletВҰ194143,
\v 6 NogahВҰ194145, NefegВҰ194146, YafiaВҰ194147,
\v 7 Elishama, Beelyada, andВҰ194149 ElifeletВҰ194151.
\s1 The defeat of the Philistines
\rem /s1 David Defeats the Philistines; Victory over the Philistines; David Conquers the Philistines; Defeat of the Philistines
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 5:17-25)
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲWhen\add* the PhilistinesВҰ194154 heardВҰ194153 that David had been anointedВҰ194157 as kingВҰ194159 over all YisraelВҰ194164, the entireВҰ194162 Philistine \add army\add* went up \add into the hill country\add* to \add вүҲeliminate\add* \add *him\add*. David \add вүҲgot this news andВҰ194153 took his army out to meet them\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the Philistines went andВҰ194180 raided the RefaimВҰ194182 valleyВҰ194181,
\v 10 and DavidВҰ194185 asked GodВҰ194186, вҖңShould I \add вүҲtake on\add* the PhilistinesВҰ194191, and will you give \add вүҲme victory over them\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲahead\add*,вҖқ YahwehВҰ194197 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңand I'll \add вүҲenable you to defeat them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ194202 they\f + \fr 14:11 \ft It's not clear who's being referred to here.\f* went up to \add what's now calledВҰ194222\add* Baal-Peratsim, andВҰ194202 David \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ194206\add* them down thereВҰ194207. David said, вҖңGod has \add вүҲused me to\add* breakВҰ194211 through my enemiesВҰ194215 like \add вүҲa flooded river breaking a dam\add*.вҖқ Therefore they namedВҰ194222 that placeВҰ194225 Baal-PeratsimВҰ194228 \add (which means вҖҳthe master burstsВҰ194217 throughвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 12 \add @The Philistines\add* abandonedВҰ194230 theirВҰ194235 \add вүҲidols\add* \add as they fled\add*, andВҰ194230 DavidВҰ194237 ordered them to be burnt.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲBut\add* \add soon\add* the PhilistinesВҰ194244 raidedВҰ194245 the valleyВҰ194246 againВҰ194243,
\v 14 and DavidВҰ194250 asked God\add 's advice\add* againВҰ194249. вҖңDon't go uphill afterВҰ194257 them,вҖқ God said, вҖң\add but\add* circle aroundВҰ194258 them and confront them in frontВҰ194262 of the balsamВҰ194263 treesВҰ194263.
\v 15 When you hearВҰ194266 the soundВҰ194269 of the marchingВҰ194270 in the tops of the balsamВҰ194272 treesВҰ194272, \add вүҲthat's when you shouldВҰ194265 attack\add*, because God will have gone out \add вүҲahead of you\add* to strikeВҰ194281 down the Philistine army.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ194287\add* DavidВҰ194288 did just as God had told him, andВҰ194287 he \add вүҲattacked\add* the PhilistinesВҰ194296 from Giveon \add вүҲall the way to\add* GezerВҰ194300.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ194302 David'sВҰ194305 reputation spread everywhere\add*, andВҰ194309 YahwehВҰ194309 \add вүҲcaused the other nationsВҰ194318 to be afraid of\add* himВҰ194313.
\c 15
\s1 Moving the box containing the agreement
\rem /s1 Preparing to Move the Ark; Getting Ready to Move the Covenant Box; The Ark Brought to Jerusalem
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add @David\add* constructed housesВҰ194323 for his \add wives\add* in the cityВҰ194324 of David. He \add also\add* preparedВҰ194326 a placeВҰ194327 for God's \add sacred\add* boxВҰ194328 andВҰ194320 erected a tent for it.
\v 2 Then DavidВҰ194337 \add вүҲordered\add*, вҖңOnly the LevitesВҰ194347 are allowed to carry God's box, because YahwehВҰ194353 choseВҰ194352 them to carry the box andВҰ194359 to ministerВҰ194359 for himВҰ194359 forever.вҖқ\x + \xo 15:2: \xt Deu 10:8.\x*
\v 3 DavidВҰ194366 assembledВҰ194365 all YisraelВҰ194371 in YerushalemВҰ194374 to bringВҰ194375 Yahweh'sВҰ194379 boxВҰ194378 uphill there to the placeВҰ194382 thatВҰ194383 he'd preparedВҰ194385 for it.
\v 4 ThenВҰ194388 he summoned Aharon's descendantsВҰ194392 andВҰ194388 these LevitesВҰ194396:
\li1
\v 5 From Kohat'sВҰ194399 descendants \add (Levi's second son)\add*: UrielВҰ194400 the leader and 120 of his relativesВҰ194402.
\li1
\v 6 From Merari'sВҰ194408 descendants \add (Levi's third son)\add*: AsayahВҰ194409 the leader and 220 of his relativesВҰ194411.
\li1
\v 7 From Gershom'sВҰ194417 descendants \add (Levi's eldest son)\add*: YoelВҰ194418 the leader and 130 of his relativesВҰ194420.
\li1
\v 8 From Elitsafan's descendants: ShemayahВҰ194427 the leader andВҰ194429 200 of his relativesВҰ194429.
\li1
\v 9 From Hevron's descendants: ElielВҰ194435 the leader andВҰ194437 eightyВҰ194438 of his relativesВҰ194437.
\li1
\v 10 From Uzziyel's descendants: Amminadav the leader and 112 of his relativesВҰ194445.
\p
\v 11 DavidВҰ194452 summoned the priestsВҰ194455 TsadokВҰ194453 and AbiatarВҰ194454 and these LevitesВҰ194456: UrielВҰ194457, AsayahВҰ194458, YoelВҰ194459, ShemayahВҰ194460, ElielВҰ194461, and AmminadavВҰ194462.
\v 12 He told them, вҖңYou are the headsВҰ194467 of the LeviteВҰ194469 clans. Consecrate yourselvesВҰ194470, you and your relativesВҰ194472, and bringВҰ194473 the boxВҰ194475 of Yisrael'sВҰ194478 godВҰ194477 YahwehВҰ194476 up to whereВҰ194481 I've preparedВҰ194481 \add a place\add* for it.
\v 13 The firstВҰ194486 \add time we tried,\add* it wasn't youВҰ194489 \add Levites, so\add* ourВҰ194492 godВҰ194492 YahwehВҰ194491 burstВҰ194490 out against us because we \add вүҲhadn't requested his instruction\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ194500\add* the priestsВҰ194501 andВҰ194502 the LevitesВҰ194502 consecratedВҰ194500 themselves to bringВҰ194503 up the \add sacred\add* boxВҰ194506 of Yisrael'sВҰ194509 godВҰ194508, YahwehВҰ194507.
\v 15 ThenВҰ194511, \add вүҲfollowing Yahweh's instructedВҰ194519 as given to MoshehВҰ194520\add* \add (MosesВҰ194520)\add*, Levi's descendantsВҰ194512 carriedВҰ194511 God's \add sacred\add* chestВҰ194516 with it's polesВҰ194524 on theirВҰ194523 shouldersВҰ194523.\x + \xo 15:15: \xt Exo 25:14.\x*
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* DavidВҰ194529 instructed the LeviteВҰ194531 leaders to assign theirВҰ194535 brothersВҰ194535 as the singersВҰ194536 with instruments of song, harps, lyres, and cymbalsВҰ194542вҖ”playing to raiseВҰ194544 a soundВҰ194543 of \add вүҲcelebration\add*.
\v 17 The LevitesВҰ194551 assigned Yoel'sВҰ194556 son HemanВҰ194553 and his relative AsafВҰ194560 (son of BerekyahВҰ194563) and Eytan (Kishayah's son, a descendantВҰ194567 of MerariВҰ194568),
\v 18 along with theirВҰ194576 \add Levite\add* cousins: Zekaryah, BenВҰ194579, YaazielВҰ194580, ShemiramotВҰ194581, Yehiel, UnniВҰ194584, Eliav, BenayahВҰ194586, MaaseyahВҰ194587, MattityahВҰ194588, ElifelehuВҰ194589, MikneyahВҰ194590, and two of the temple gatekeepersВҰ194594, Oved-Edom and YeielВҰ194593.
\v 19 HemanВҰ194597, AsafВҰ194598, and EtanВҰ194599 \add вүҲsang and also played\add* bronzeВҰ194601 cymbalsВҰ194600.
