\v 3 \add вүҲBut that nightВҰ195322 GodВҰ195327 spoke\add* to NatanВҰ195330,
\v 4 вҖңGo andВҰ195334 tell my servantВҰ195338 DavidВҰ195337 that YahwehВҰ195341 saysВҰ195340 this: You yourself \add вүҲwon'tВҰ195342 be the one to\add* buildВҰ195344 a residence for me to live in,
\v 5 because I haven't lived in a building from the day that I broughtВҰ195358 YisraelВҰ195361 \add out of Egypt\add* untilВҰ195362 todayвҖ”I've \add вүҲmoved from place to place and tent to tent\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲAs I travelled with all the IsraelisВҰ195385\add*, \add вүҲdid I ever complain to any of Yisrael's leaders\add* who I'd commandedВҰ195387 to shepherdВҰ195388 my peopleВҰ195391, \add вүҲand ask them\add*, вҖҳWhy haven't youВҰ195396 all builtВҰ195396 a houseВҰ195398 of cedarВҰ195399 for me?вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ195401 now you should tell\add* my servantВҰ195405 DavidВҰ195406 that army commander YahwehВҰ195410 saysВҰ195409 this: IВҰ195412 myself tookВҰ195413 you from the pastureВҰ195416, from behind the sheepВҰ195420, to be a leader over my peopleВҰ195424 YisraelВҰ195425.
\v 8 I've always been with you whereverВҰ195430 you've gone, and I've \add вүҲdefeated all yourВҰ195438 enemiesВҰ195437 who were attacking you\add*, and I'll \add вүҲmake you famous like some of the greatestВҰ195443 people in the world\add*.
\v 9 I'll set a place for my peopleВҰ195449 YisraelВҰ195450, and I'll plantВҰ195451 them, and they'll settle \add @in that place\add* and \add вүҲnot need to be fearful againВҰ195456\add*. \add вүҲViolent groups won'tВҰ195454 continue to trouble them like they've done before\add*,
\v 10 and \add вүҲever since the time that I put heroes and leaders\add* over my peopleВҰ195473 YisraelВҰ195474. ThenВҰ195467 I'll humble all your enemiesВҰ195480. \add вүҲIn addition\add*, I declareВҰ195481 to you that YahwehВҰ195487 will buildВҰ195484 \add вүҲa dynasty\add* for you.
\v 11 \add вүҲWhen your time on earth is up and it's time to join your deceased ancestorsВҰ195497\add*, thenВҰ195489 I'll raiseВҰ195498 up one of your sonsВҰ195505 and establishВҰ195506 his kingdomВҰ195509.
\v 12 He'll \add вүҲbe the one to\add* buildВҰ195512 a temple for me andВҰ195516 establishВҰ195516 a \add вүҲdynasty that will last\add* forever.
\v 13 I myself will be a fatherВҰ195528 to him, and he'll be a son to me, and I won'tВҰ195535 \add вүҲcease my loyal commitment to him like I ended it with yourВҰ195543 predecessorВҰ195543\add*.\x + \xo 17:13: \xt 2Cor 6:18; Heb 1:5.\x*
\v 14 I'll \add вүҲconfirmВҰ195545 his rule over my temple and my kingdomВҰ195547 forever, and his ruling dynasty will last\add* forever.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 So NatanВҰ195566 \add вүҲpassed all of that on\add* to DavidВҰ195569.
