\v 3 Next DavidВҰ195820 \add вүҲattacked andВҰ195819 defeatedВҰ195819\add* King HadadezerВҰ195823 of Tsovah-HamatВҰ195827, when \add вүҲthat kingВҰ195824 had tried enforce his control\add* at the EuphratesВҰ195833 \add River\add*.
\v 4 David capturedВҰ195835 1,000 chariots, 7,000 horsemen, andВҰ195835 20,000 foot-soldiers from him. And David hamstrungВҰ195847 all but one hundredВҰ195856 of the chariotВҰ195853 \add horsesВҰ195853\add*.
\p
\v 5 When the Arameans \add (or, SyriansВҰ195860)\add* cameВҰ195859 from DamascusВҰ195861 to helpВҰ195862 King HadadezerВҰ195863, DavidВҰ195867 struckВҰ195866 killed 22,000 of the Arameans.
\v 6 ThenВҰ195875 David \add вүҲestablished forces\add* in the Aramean \add town\add* of DamascusВҰ195878, andВҰ195875 the ArameansВҰ195877 became servants to David, \add вүҲtaking him\add* \add regular\add* tributeВҰ195884. \add вүҲSoВҰ195875\add* YahwehВҰ195886 \add вүҲhelped\add* David \add вүҲwhereverВҰ195889\add* heВҰ195890 wentВҰ195890.
\v 7 DavidВҰ195893 tookВҰ195892 the goldВҰ195896 shieldsВҰ195895 thatВҰ195897 were used by Hadadezer'sВҰ195901 servantsВҰ195900 andВҰ195902 broughtВҰ195902 them to YerushalemВҰ195903.
\v 8 \add *He\add* also tookВҰ195909 a lot of bronze from Hadadezer'sВҰ195908 citiesВҰ195907 of Tibhat and Kun. (\add Later,\add* Shelomoh/SolomonВҰ195917 used itВҰ195914 to make the \add вүҲhuge bronze basin called вҖҳthe seaВҰ195920вҖҷ, along with its\add* pillarsВҰ195924 and other bronze items.)\x + \xo 18:8: \xt 1Ki 7:40-47; 2Ch 4:11-18.\x*
\p
\v 9 When King To'u from HamatВҰ195933 heard that DavidВҰ195936 \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ195935 the entireВҰ195939\add* the army of King HadadezerВҰ195942 from Tsovah,
\v 10 he sentВҰ195947 his son HadoramВҰ195950 to King David carrying various items of goldВҰ195978, silverВҰ195979, and bronzeВҰ195980. \add Hadorom went\add* to askВҰ195958 \add @David\add* for peaceВҰ195962 and to bless him because he'd foughtВҰ195966 against Hadadezer and struck him down, because To'u had \add also\add* \add вүҲbeen at war\add* with Hadadezer.
\v 11 King DavidВҰ195987 consecratedВҰ195985 that to YahwehВҰ195988, along with the goldВҰ195992 and silverВҰ195991 that he'd broughtВҰ195994 back from \add вүҲother\add* nationsВҰ195997: from EdomВҰ195998, from Moav, from the \add вүҲAmmonites\add*, from the PhilistinesВҰ196002, and from \add вүҲthe AmalekitesВҰ196003\add*.
\p
\v 12 Avshai (whose \add mother\add* was Tseruyah) defeated EdomВҰ196012 in the Salt ValleyВҰ196013, \add killing\add* eighteenВҰ196015 thousandВҰ196017 \add of them\add*.\x + \xo 18:12: \xt Psa 60 header.\x*
\v 13 ThenВҰ196019 \add @David\add* stationed garrisonsВҰ196021 in Edom, andВҰ196019 all Edom became his servants. And YahwehВҰ196029 saved David in all whereВҰ196034 heВҰ196035 wentВҰ196035.
\rem /s1 David's Officials; David's Administration
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ196037\add* DavidВҰ196038 ruled over all YisraelВҰ196043 and administered justiceВҰ196046 and \add вүҲdid what was rightВҰ196047\add* for all his peopleВҰ196050.
\v 15 Tseruyah's son Yoav led the army, andВҰ196059 Ahilud'sВҰ196062 son YehoshafatВҰ196059 was the recordВҰ196063 keeper.
\v 16 Ahituv'sВҰ196068 son Tsadok and Avyatar'sВҰ196072 son Ahimelek were priestsВҰ196073, and ShavshaВҰ196074 was the secretaryВҰ196075.
\v 17 Yehoyada's son Benayah \add вүҲsupervised\add* the Keretites and Feletites \add who were David's bodyguards\add*, and David's sonsВҰ196085 \add вүҲwere his leading officialsВҰ196088\add*.
\c 19
\s1 The defeat of the Ammonites and Arameans
\rem /s1 The Battle Against the Ammonites; David Defeats the Ammonites and the Syrians; David Defeats the Ammonites; Defeat of the Ammonites and Arameans
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 10:1-19)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSome time later\add*, the Ammonite King NahashВҰ196098 died and his son \add Hanun\add* \add вүҲbecameВҰ196103 their king\add*
\v 2 andВҰ196107 David said, вҖңI'll show loyal commitment to Nahash'sВҰ196118 son Hanun, because his father \add вүҲwas good to me\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ196107\add* David sent messengersВҰ196127 to comfort him concerning his father's \add death\add*. \add вүҲHowever,\add* when David'sВҰ196108 servantsВҰ196133 \add вүҲentered Ammonite territory\add* to comfort Hanun,
\v 3 the Ammonite leadersВҰ196147 \add вүҲasked their new king\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDo you think that\add* David'sВҰ196153 \add really\add* sending comfortersВҰ196162 to honourВҰ196152 yourВҰ196157 father? \add вүҲWouldn't it be more likely that he sentВҰ196160 his servantsВҰ196170 to explore andВҰ196146 spy out the land in order to overthrowВҰ196166 you\add*?вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSo\add* \add King\add* HanunВҰ196175 tookВҰ196174 David'sВҰ196179 servantsВҰ196178, and \add had their beards\add* shavedВҰ196180 off, plus he cut \add вүҲoff the bottom half of their robes to expose their\add* buttocks, and then he sentВҰ196189 them \add вүҲhome\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲSome people quickly informed DavidВҰ196193 what had happened\add*, so he sent \add messengers\add* to meet the men (because they were very much humiliatedВҰ196203) andВҰ196191 to tell them, вҖңStay \add there\add* in Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add* untilВҰ196209 your beardsВҰ196213 grow \add out\add*, thenВҰ196191 returnВҰ196214 \add here\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲBy thenВҰ196216\add*, the Ammonites \add вүҲrealised that they had greatly insulted\add* \add King\add* DavidВҰ196223, \add вүҲso\add* \add King\add* HanunВҰ196225 and the Ammonites sentВҰ196224 thirty tonnes of silverВҰ196231 to hire chariotsВҰ196243 and horsemenВҰ196244 from Aram-Naharayim, Aram-Maakah, and Tsovah.
\v 7 They hiredВҰ196246 32,000 chariotsВҰ196251, \add вүҲas well as\add* the kingВҰ196254 of Maakah and his army. They \add all\add* came and \add вүҲset up their camps near\add* Meydeva, \add вүҲplus they were joined by\add* the Ammonites \add themselves\add* coming out of their citiesВҰ196266 ready for battleВҰ196268.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲWhen\add* DavidВҰ196272 heard \add about that\add*, he sentВҰ196273 Yoav \add вүҲwith the entireВҰ196278\add* army.
\v 9 ThenВҰ196283 the AmmonitesВҰ196285 marched out andВҰ196283 deployed ready for battleВҰ196287 at the entranceВҰ196288 to their cityВҰ196289, while kingsВҰ196290 who had comeВҰ196293 were over in the countrysideВҰ196295 \add with their men\add*.
\p
\v 10 Yoav \add quickly\add* realised that \add вүҲhe'd have to fight on two fronts, so\add* he choseВҰ196308 Yisrael's best warriors andВҰ196297 set them out to faceВҰ196302 the ArameansВҰ196315 \add (SyriansВҰ196315)\add*,
\v 11 while he placed the remaining men (under the control of his \add older brother\add* Avshai) out againstВҰ196325 the Ammonites.
\v 12 Yoav told them, вҖңIf the ArameansВҰ196334 are too strong for me, then you \add вүҲcan come to rescue me\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ196329\add* if the Ammonites \add вүҲstart to gain on you\add*, then I'll \add come to\add* rescue you.
\v 13 We must be strongВҰ196347 and fight hard to defend our peopleВҰ196351 and our citiesВҰ196353 \add вүҲthat belong to\add* our godВҰ196354. YahwehВҰ196355 will do \add вүҲwhat he considers to be\add* goodВҰ196356.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ196360\add* Yoav \add вүҲadvanced hisВҰ196370 troops to attack the Arameans, but the Arameans fled away from them\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲWhen\add* the Ammonites sawВҰ196374 that the ArameansВҰ196378 had fled, \add вүҲthey also fled from Avshai andВҰ196372 withdrew into\add* the cityВҰ196387, \add вүҲso\add* Yoav wentВҰ196386 back to YerushalemВҰ196390.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲWhen the Arameans\add* sawВҰ196393 thatВҰ196405 they were defeatedВҰ196396 \add вүҲby\add* YisraelВҰ196398, they sentВҰ196399 messengersВҰ196400 to bring \add вүҲmore Arameans from across the Euphrates riverВҰ196407, led by\add* Shofak, the commanderВҰ196409 of Hadadezer'sВҰ196412 army.
\v 17 \add вүҲWhen\add* that was reported to DavidВҰ196416, he gatheredВҰ196417 all YisraelВҰ196422 andВҰ196415 crossed the YordanВҰ196424. They positioned themselves against the ArameansВҰ196432 who thenВҰ196415 foughtВҰ196434 against them.
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ196437 the ArameansВҰ196438 fled away from the Israelis\add*, and DavidВҰ196442 killed sevenВҰ196444 thousand chariotВҰ196446 \add drivers\add* and fortyВҰ196447 thousand men on footВҰ196450, as well as killing Shofak their army commanderВҰ196453.
\v 19 When Hadadezer'sВҰ196460 servantsВҰ196459 sawВҰ196458 that \add вүҲYisraelВҰ196464 had defeatedВҰ196462 them\add*, they made peaceВҰ196465 with DavidВҰ196468 andВҰ196458 \add вүҲbecameВҰ196469 his subjectsВҰ196469, so\add* AramВҰ196473 \add (SyriaВҰ196473)\add* wasn't willingВҰ196472 to helpВҰ196474 the Ammonites \add militarily\add* any more.
\c 20
\s1 David captures Rabbah
\rem /s1 Siege and Capture of Rabbah; David Captures Rabbah; The Capture of Rabbah
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 12:26-31)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲThen in the spring when kingsВҰ196490 often march out to war\add*, Yoav led the army out for war and he devastated the land of the Ammonites. Then he reached \add the capital,\add* Rabbah, and he besieged it while DavidВҰ196510 stayed in YerushalemВҰ196512. Yoav \add вүҲdefeated\add* Rabbah and \add вүҲdemolished the city\add*.\x + \xo 20:1: \xt 2Sam 11:1.\x*
\v 2 ThenВҰ196520 DavidВҰ196521 took theirВҰ196526 king's crown off his headвҖ”it was goldВҰ196534 with a valuable gemstone set in out, andВҰ196520 \add вүҲweighedВҰ196531 thirty kilograms\add*. HeВҰ196542 put \add @the crown\add* on his own head, plus he took a very large amount of plunder out of the cityВҰ196544.
\v 3 ThenВҰ196549 they took all the people out of the city and \add вүҲforced them to work\add* with saws and iron picksВҰ196558, and axesВҰ196560. DavidВҰ196563 did thatВҰ196552 for the people of all the Ammonite citiesВҰ196565, thenВҰ196549 he returnedВҰ196569 to YerushalemВҰ196574 with his army.
\s1 Battles against Gittites
\rem /s1 Battles against the Philistines; Battles against Philistine Giants; War With the Philistines; Exploits against the Philistines
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 21:15-22)
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSome time later,\add* war brokeВҰ196581 out with the PhilistinesВҰ196586 at GezerВҰ196583, then Sibbekai the HushatiteВҰ196590 struckВҰ196588 down SippaiВҰ196593, from the descendantsВҰ196594 of the Refaim, and they were subduedВҰ196596.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ196598 there was another battleВҰ196601 with the PhilistinesВҰ196604, andВҰ196598 Yair'sВҰ196609 son ElhananВҰ196606 \add вүҲkilledВҰ196605\add* LahmiВҰ196613 the brotherВҰ196614 of Goliyat \add (GoliathВҰ196615)\add*\x + \xo 20:5: \xt 1Sam 17:4-7.\x* the GittiteВҰ196616 \add (i.e., from Gat)\add*, even though his spearВҰ196618 shaft was \add as thick\add* as the beam of a weaver'sВҰ196620 \add loom\add*.
\v 6 There was also war at GatВҰ196626 where there was a \add вүҲvery tall manВҰ196629 with six fingersВҰ196631 on each hand andВҰ196622 six toes on each foot who was also a descendant\add* of Rafa.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhen\add* he insulted YisraelВҰ196646, Shimea'sВҰ196651 son Yonatan killedВҰ196647 him. (Shimea was one of David'sВҰ196653 \add older\add* brothersВҰ196652.)
\p
\v 8 Those were the descendants of Rafa from GatВҰ196658 who were killed by DavidВҰ196662 and he men.
\c 21
\s1 David orders a census
\rem /s1 David Numbers the Fighting Men; The Census and Plague; David Takes a Census; David's census
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 24:1-25)
\s2 Yoav doesn't want to do the census
\p
\v 1 Then a trouble-maker went against Yisrael \add вүҲby\add* encouraging DavidВҰ196676 \add вүҲto take a census of\add* Yisrael,
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ196682\add* DavidВҰ196683 \add вүҲordered\add* Yoav and \add вүҲthe other officials\add*, вҖңGo \add and\add* countВҰ196692 YisraelВҰ196695 from Be'er-Sheva \add in the south\add* and as far \add north\add* as DanВҰ196700, \add вүҲthenВҰ196682 come and tell me so that I'll knowВҰ196703 how many warriors I have\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңMy master, the kingВҰ196721, may YahwehВҰ196720 \add вүҲmultiply his peopleВҰ196714 one hundredВҰ196717 timesВҰ196718 over\add*. Aren't they all \add *your\add* servantsВҰ196724?вҖқ Yoav \add diplomatically\add* \add вүҲqueried\add*, вҖң\add SoВҰ196708\add* why does my master \add вүҲwant to do\add* this? Why should \add вүҲhe bring judgement on\add* YisraelВҰ196732?вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲButВҰ196734 the kingВҰ196736 insisted, so Yoav was forced to go andВҰ196734 survey the entireВҰ196744 country\add*. ThenВҰ196734 he returned to YerushalemВҰ196748
\v 5 and \add вүҲreported the numbersВҰ196754\add* to DavidВҰ196760. YisraelВҰ196764 had 1.1 million sword-wielding men, and Yehudah had 470 thousandВҰ196766.
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add @Yoav\add* had \add intentionally\add* not counted \add the tribes of\add* Levi andВҰ196782 BenyaminВҰ196782, because \add *he\add* was horrified by the king's command.
\s2 Punishment for the census
\rem /s1 Judgment for David's Sin
\p
\v 7 God \add вүҲwas displeasedВҰ196796 by what David had ordered, andВҰ196796 he punished\add* YisraelВҰ196806,
\v 8 and DavidВҰ196810 saidВҰ196809 to God, вҖңI've \add вүҲdisobeyed you badly by doing that\add*. Please \add вүҲforgive yourВҰ196829 servantВҰ196829 for his disobedience\add*, because I've \add вүҲbeen very stupid\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ196836 told David'sВҰ196841 prophet GadВҰ196839,
\v 10 вҖңGo and tell DavidВҰ196848 that YahwehВҰ196852 saysВҰ196851 this: \add вүҲI'll give you threeВҰ196853 optionsвҖ”chooseВҰ196857 one of them and that's what I'll\add* do to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ196866\add* GadВҰ196867 wentВҰ196866 to DavidВҰ196870 andВҰ196871 told his, вҖңYahwehВҰ196876 saysВҰ196875 that you must choose \add one of these punishments\add*:
\v 12 either three yearsВҰ196884 of famineВҰ196885, or three monthsВҰ196889 of beingВҰ196890 overcome by your enemies' \add вүҲarmies\add*, or three daysВҰ196901 of Yahweh's вҖҳswordвҖҷ of pestilenceВҰ196904 in the land and the Yahweh's messengerВҰ196906 \add вүҲbringingВҰ196917 destructionВҰ196908\add* across all of Yisrael's territoryВҰ196911. \add вүҲSo now, tell me what answer I should take\add* back to the one who sent me?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add Oh,\add* that's very distressingВҰ196929,вҖқ DavidВҰ196925 \add вүҲreplied\add* to GadВҰ196928, вҖңbut please don'tВҰ196947 let me fall into the handsВҰ196944 of \add вүҲmy enemies\add*. YahwehВҰ196938 \add вүҲis very merciful, so please let him be the one to punish me directly\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ196951\add* YahwehВҰ196952 \add вүҲsent a disease\add* throughout YisraelВҰ196954 andВҰ196951 seventyВҰ196957 thousandВҰ196958 IsraeliВҰ196956 men \add вүҲdied\add*.
\v 15 ThenВҰ196961 God sentВҰ196961 a messenger to destroy YerushalemВҰ196966, and \add вүҲwhile the disease was still spreading\add* Yahweh \add вүҲlooked down\add* and relented about the tragedy, and he told to the destroying messenger, вҖңEnough! Now release your handВҰ196981.вҖқ Now Yahweh's messenger \add happened to be\add* standingВҰ196984 at the threshingВҰ196987 floorВҰ196987 of OrnanВҰ196988 the Yevusite.
\p
\v 16 \add As\add* David \add вүҲlooked up\add*, he sawВҰ196997 Yahweh's messengerВҰ197000 standingВҰ197002 between the earthВҰ197004 and the heavensВҰ197006, holding his swordВҰ197007 stretchedВҰ197010 out over YerushalemВҰ197013. Then David and the eldersВҰ197016 who were \add all\add* dressed in sackclothВҰ197018, fell \add вүҲto their knees and bowed their facesВҰ197021 to the ground\add*.
\v 17 ThenВҰ197023 DavidВҰ197024 \add вүҲasked\add* GodВҰ197046, вҖңWasn't it me myself who said to countВҰ197031 the people? It's me who \add вүҲdisobeyed and clearly did what was wrongВҰ197039\add*, but theseВҰ197041 sheepВҰ197042, what have they done? YahwehВҰ197045 my godВҰ197046, pleaseВҰ197048 \add вүҲdirect your punishment\add* against me and \add вүҲmy extended family\add*, but \add вүҲdon'tВҰ197028 continue this\add* plagueВҰ197055 on your people.вҖқ
\rem /s1 David's Altar and Sacrifice; David Builds an Altar
\p
\v 18 Then Yahweh's messengerВҰ197058 told GadВҰ197063 to tell DavidВҰ197065 that \add *he\add* should \add вүҲbuild\add* an altarВҰ197071 to Yahweh at the threshingВҰ197073 floorВҰ197073 of OrnanВҰ197074 the Yevusite.
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ197077\add* DavidВҰ197078 went up \add to that place when heВҰ197083 heard\add* \add вүҲGad'sВҰ197081 messageВҰ197079 that was delivered\add* in Yahweh'sВҰ197085 nameВҰ197084.
\v 20 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* OrnanВҰ197088 was threshingВҰ197098 wheatВҰ197099, and he turnedВҰ197087 and sawВҰ197089 \add Yahweh's\add* messengerВҰ197092 and he and his fourВҰ197093 sonsВҰ197094 who were with him \add quickly\add* hid \add вүҲbehind something\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhen David arrived there,\add* OrnanВҰ197105 sawВҰ197108 him and left the threshingВҰ197115 floorВҰ197115 and \add вүҲknelt\add* in front of David and bowedВҰ197116 his faceВҰ197118 to the groundВҰ197119.
\v 22 ThenВҰ197121 DavidВҰ197122 \add вүҲasked\add* OrnanВҰ197125, вҖңGive me this placeВҰ197129 with its threshingВҰ197130 floorВҰ197130, andВҰ197121 I'll buildВҰ197131 an altarВҰ197134 to YahwehВҰ197135 on it. \add вүҲSell it to me\add* at the full priceВҰ197136, so the plagueВҰ197141 against the peopleВҰ197143 will be stoppedВҰ197140.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 вҖңMy masterВҰ197154 the kingВҰ197155, takeВҰ197150 \add вүҲanything that you want\add*,вҖқ OrnanВҰ197146 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңListen, I'll donate the cattle for the burntВҰ197161 offerings and the threshingВҰ197162 sledgesВҰ197162 for firewood, and the wheatВҰ197164 for the offeringвҖ”all \add вүҲat no charge\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңNo, I'll most definitely pay the full priceВҰ197178,вҖқ King DavidВҰ197171 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ197169\add*. вҖңI couldn't offer a burntВҰ197189 offering to YahwehВҰ197187 \add вүҲif it hadn't cost me anything\add*.вҖқ
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ197192\add* DavidВҰ197193 paid OrnanВҰ197194 sixВҰ197199 hundredВҰ197200 goldВҰ197197 pieces for \add &his\add* place,
\v 26 and he builtВҰ197202 an altar to Yahweh thereВҰ197203 and offered burnt offerings and peaceВҰ197209 offerings on it. He calledВҰ197210 to Yahweh, and \add @Yahweh\add* answeredВҰ197214 him with fireВҰ197215 from the heavensВҰ197218 on that altar of the burnt offering.
\p
\v 27 Then YahwehВҰ197225 spoke to \add &his\add* messengerВҰ197226 who then returned his swordВҰ197228 to his sheathВҰ197231.
\s1 The location for the future temple
\rem /s1 The Place Chosen for the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\v 28 When DavidВҰ197236 sawВҰ197235 that YahwehВҰ197240 had answeredВҰ197239 him at (the Yevusite) Ornan'sВҰ197242 threshingВҰ197241 floorВҰ197241, then he sacrificedВҰ197244 thereВҰ197245.
\v 29 \add вүҲAt that timeВҰ197256\add*, Yahweh's \add sacredВҰ197247\add* tentВҰ197247 that MoshehВҰ197252 \add (MosesВҰ197252)\add* had made in the wildernessВҰ197253, andВҰ197254 the altarВҰ197254 for burntВҰ197255 sacrifices, were \add вүҲon a hill used for worship near\add* GibeonВҰ197259 \add city\add*.
\v 30 DavidВҰ197264 wasn't able to goВҰ197265 there to \add вүҲask God's direction\add* because he was terrifiedВҰ197270 of Yahweh's messenger'sВҰ197273 swordВҰ197272.
\c 22
\p
\v 1 Then DavidВҰ197278 saidВҰ197277, вҖңThis is \add now\add* the residence of YahwehВҰ197282 God, and this is the altarВҰ197286 for Yisrael's burntВҰ197287 \add #offering\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The preparation of standing up of temple
\rem /s1 Preparations for the Temple; Preparation for the temple; Preparations for Building the Temple; David Prepares to Build the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 2 Then DavidВҰ197292 saidВҰ197291 to gather the foreigners who \add вүҲlived\add* in IsraelВҰ197299, and he assigned \add вүҲthem the job of\add* hewing out cut stonesВҰ197303 to buildВҰ197305 the residenceВҰ197296 for God.
\v 3 HeВҰ197317 preparedВҰ197316 a large quantity of iron for the door \add вүҲhinges andВҰ197309 fittings\add*, so much brass that it couldn't be weighedВҰ197321,
\v 4 and innumerable cedar logs that the Tsidonians and the Tsorians \add (SidoniansВҰ197329 and TyriansВҰ197330)\add* broughtВҰ197328 in for DavidВҰ197334.
\v 5 David saidВҰ197337, вҖңMy son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ197339)\add* is young and tender, and the houseВҰ197343 to be builtВҰ197344 for YahwehВҰ197345 must be \add вүҲimpressive for the sake of his reputation\add* and for beauty in all the landsВҰ197353 \add so\add* I'll prepare for it now.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* David prepared a large amount before \add вүҲhe died\add*.
\rem /s1 David's Charge to Solomon and the Leaders
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ197363 David calledВҰ197363 for his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ197364)\add*, andВҰ197366 ordered himВҰ197366 to buildВҰ197367 a residence for Yisrael's godВҰ197370 YahwehВҰ197369.
\v 7 DavidВҰ197375 told \add *him\add*, вҖңMy son, I wanted to buildВҰ197384 a temple to honour my godВҰ197388 YahwehВҰ197387,\x + \xo 22:7-10: \xt 2Sam 7:1-16; 1Ch 17:1-14.\x*
\v 8 \add вүҲbut\add* YahwehВҰ197394 \add вүҲgave me this messageВҰ197392\add*, вҖҳYou've fought a lot of battles andВҰ197390 shed a large amount of blood, \add so\add* you won'tВҰ197402 be the one who'll buildВҰ197404 a residence \add вүҲto honour me\add*вҖ”you've shed too much blood on the ground \add вүҲin myВҰ197412 sightВҰ197412\add*.вҖҷ
\v 9 \add He told me,\add* вҖҳListen, you'll have a son who'll be a manВҰ197421 of peace. I'll give him relief from all his enemiesВҰ197427 from the surrounding regions. That's why he'll be called вҖҳShelomohвҖҷ \add (which sounds like вҖҳShalomвҖҷвҖ”the Hebrew word for peace)\add*, and I'll give peace and quietnessВҰ197434 to YisraelВҰ197438 during his lifetime.
\v 10 He'll be the one to buildВҰ197443 a residence for me, and he himself will become my son, and I'll become his fatherВҰ197454, and I'll establishВҰ197455 the throneВҰ197456 of his kingdomВҰ197457 over YisraelВҰ197460 forever.вҖҷ
\p
\v 11 вҖңNow, my son, may Yahweh be with you, and may you be successfulВҰ197470 and buildВҰ197471 a residence for Yahweh your godВҰ197474, just as he said you would.
\v 12 \add вүҲI also ask\add* Yahweh to give you insightВҰ197484 and understandingВҰ197485, and give you chargeВҰ197486 over YisraelВҰ197489 so that you can keep your godВҰ197495 Yahweh's regulations.
\v 13 Then you'll succeedВҰ197498, if you are careful to follow the instructions and the directions thatВҰ197509 YahwehВҰ197511 commandedВҰ197510 MoshehВҰ197514 \add (MosesВҰ197514)\add* concerning YisraelВҰ197517. Be strongВҰ197518 and courageousВҰ197519. Don't be afraidВҰ197522 or discouraged.\x + \xo 22:13: \xt Josh 1:6-9.\x*
\p
\v 14 Now, see, \add ?вүҲdespite many battles\add*, I've prepared the following for Yahweh's residence: three thousand tonnes of goldВҰ197533 and thirty thousand tonnes of silverВҰ197538, along with too much bronzeВҰ197542 and iron to weighВҰ197545, and timberВҰ197549 and \add cut\add* stonesВҰ197550. Plus you'll be able to add more.
\v 15 \add вүҲYou'll have plenty of skilledВҰ197565 workers including those who work with stoneВҰ197561 andВҰ197555 those who work with wood\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲThen there'sВҰ197574 so many skilled with goldВҰ197570 and silverВҰ197571, and bronzeВҰ197572 and iron. So get organised and get started\add*, and may YahwehВҰ197579 be with youВҰ197580.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ197582 DavidВҰ197583 ordered all the IsraeliВҰ197586 officialsВҰ197586 to assist his son Shelomoh, \add saying\add*,
\v 18 вҖңIsn't Yahweh your godВҰ197594 with you all, and hasn't he given peace to you all from all around, because he's \add вүҲallowed me to take control of this region, and this area has been subduedВҰ197606 with the help\add* of Yahweh and his peopleВҰ197611.
\v 19 Now, \add вүҲdedicate your mindВҰ197615 and strength to request advice from your godВҰ197619 Yahweh, then get organised and buildВҰ197621 the sanctuaryВҰ197624 of Yahweh God so you can bring the box containing Yahweh's agreement to the residence to be builtВҰ197638 to honour Yahweh's nameВҰ197639, and bring God's sacred items\add*.вҖқ
\c 23
\rem /s1 Families of the Levites and Their Functions; Duties of the Levites; The Levites
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲBy then DavidВҰ197644 was old and coming to the end of his life\add*, and heВҰ197645 made his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ197651)\add* kingВҰ197648 over YisraelВҰ197655.\x + \xo 23:1: \xt 1Ki 1:1-40.\x*
\s1 The Levite families and their assignments
\rem /s1 The Work of the Levites
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 2 ThenВҰ197657 \add @David\add* gathered all the IsraeliВҰ197663 officials and the priestsВҰ197664 and LevitesВҰ197665.
\v 3 Counting the LeviteВҰ197668 males that were thirty years old andВҰ197667 older, they found there were thirty-eight thousandВҰ197679 menВҰ197676.
\v 4 \add David assigned\add* twenty-four thousand of them to supervise the work at Yahweh's temple, sixВҰ197694 thousand to be officialsВҰ197692 and judgesВҰ197693,
\v 5 four thousand to be gatekeepersВҰ197699, andВҰ197697 four thousand to praiseВҰ197707 YahwehВҰ197703 using the musical instrumentsВҰ197704 thatВҰ197705 he'd provided.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ197709\add* DavidВҰ197710 dividedВҰ197709 \add @the Levites\add* into divisionsВҰ197711 accordingВҰ197713 to \add their ancestry through\add* Levi'sВҰ197714 sonsВҰ197713 GershonВҰ197715, KohatВҰ197716, andВҰ197717 MerariВҰ197717.
\s1 The Gershonites
\rem /s1 The Gershonites; Gershonites
\p
\v 7 The Gershonites \add included\add* LadanВҰ197721 andВҰ197722 ShimeiВҰ197722.
\v 8 Ladan'sВҰ197726 threeВҰ197731 sonsВҰ197725 were: YehielВҰ197728 (the oldest), ZetamВҰ197729, and YoelВҰ197730.
\v 9 Shimei'sВҰ197735\f + \fr 23:9 \ft Possibly the wrong name got into the Hebrew here, because it disagrees with v10.\f* threeВҰ197740 sonsВҰ197734 were: Shelomot, HazielВҰ197738, and HaranВҰ197739. (They were leaders of Ladan'sВҰ197744 clans.)
\v 10 Shimei'sВҰ197748 four sons were: Yahat, ZinaВҰ197750,\f + \fr 23:10 \ft Some ancient translations have Zizah here, which would seem to fit better with v11.\f* YeushВҰ197751, and BeriahВҰ197752.
\v 11 (YahatВҰ197761 was the head, and ZizahВҰ197763 was secondВҰ197764. YeushВҰ197765 and BeriahВҰ197766 were \add вүҲgrouped together as one family unit as they only had few descendants\add*.)
\s2 The Kohatites
\rem /s1 Kohathites; The Kohathites
\p
\v 12 Kohat'sВҰ197779 fourВҰ197784 sonsВҰ197778 were: AmramВҰ197780, Yitshar, Hevron, andВҰ197783 UzzielВҰ197783.
\v 13 Amram'sВҰ197788 sons were Aharon and MoshehВҰ197790 \add (AaronВҰ197789 and MosesВҰ197790)\add*. Aharon \add вүҲand his future male descendants were permanently appointed\add* to consecrateВҰ197793 the most sacredВҰ197794 things, to burn incenseВҰ197802, to ministerВҰ197805 to YahwehВҰ197804, and to blessВҰ197806 his nameВҰ197807.\x + \xo 23:13: \xt Exo 28:1.\x*
\v 14 MoshehВҰ197812 \add was known as\add* \add вүҲa manВҰ197813 who served\add* God, andВҰ197812 his descendants were included with the \add other\add* Levites.
\v 15 Mosheh'sВҰ197823 sonsВҰ197822 were GershomВҰ197824 andВҰ197825 EliezerВҰ197825.
\v 16 Gershom'sВҰ197828 eldest son was ShevuelВҰ197829.
\v 17 Eliezer'sВҰ197835 only son was Rehavyah, but Rehavyah \add went on to\add* have many sons.
\p
\v 18 Yitshar'sВҰ197850 eldest son was ShelomotВҰ197851.
\v 19 Hevron's sonsВҰ197855 \add вүҲfrom oldest to youngest\add* were: Yeriyyah, AmaryahВҰ197859, YahazielВҰ197861, andВҰ197863 Yekamean.
\v 20 Uzziel'sВҰ197867 sonsВҰ197866 were MikahВҰ197868 andВҰ197870 YishshiyahВҰ197870.
\s2 The Merarites
\rem /s1 The Merarites; Merarites
\p
\v 21 Merari'sВҰ197875 sibs were Mahli and MushiВҰ197877, \add and\add* Mahli sons were EleazarВҰ197880 and KishВҰ197881.
\v 22 EleazarВҰ197884 died without having any sons, \add so\add* his brother Kish'sВҰ197897 sons marriedВҰ197894 his daughtersВҰ197893 \add (to continue the family name)\add*.
\v 23 MushiВҰ197901 had threeВҰ197905 sonsВҰ197900: MahliВҰ197902, EderВҰ197903, and YerimotВҰ197904.
\p
\v 24 Those were Levi'sВҰ197910 descendantsВҰ197908 \add вүҲby their clans and their appointments, who did the workВҰ197921 of servingВҰ197921 in Yahweh's temple once theyВҰ197915 reached twentyВҰ197925 years old\add*,
\v 25 because DavidВҰ197931 had saidВҰ197930, вҖңYisrael'sВҰ197936 godВҰ197934 YahwehВҰ197933 has givenВҰ197932 peace to his peopleВҰ197937, andВҰ197938 he'll \add now\add* live foreverВҰ197942 in YerushalemВҰ197939,
\v 26 so the LevitesВҰ197945 won'tВҰ197946 need to carryВҰ197948 the \add sacredВҰ197951\add* tentВҰ197951 anymore, along with all its equipment.вҖқ\x + \xo 23:26: \xt Deu 10:8.\x*
\v 27 \add вүҲSo one of David'sВҰ197961 final instructions had been to count the Levite men who were twentyВҰ197969 years old andВҰ197971 over\add*,
\v 28 because their work was to \add вүҲassistВҰ197975\add* Aharon's descendantsВҰ197977 in their work in Yahweh's temple. They \add вүҲwere in charge\add* of the temple courtyardsВҰ197984 and siderooms, \add вүҲin charge of the purificationВҰ197990 ceremonies\add*, and did other work at the temple.\x + \xo 23:28-32: \xt Num 3:5-9.\x*
\v 29 \add вүЎThey were also in charge of\add* the sacred bread, as well as the fine flourВҰ198001 for the offering, the wafersВҰ198003 of bread without rising agent, the baking pans, and \add вүҲall the measuringВҰ198009 and mixing of ingredients\add*.
\p
\v 30 Every morning and every eveningВҰ198019 \add @the Levites\add* stood and praisedВҰ198016 YahwehВҰ198017.
\v 31 They would also do that on the rest days, and at the new moon celebrations and during the other religious festivalsВҰ198027. \add вүҲThere were regulations about how many of them must always be on duty serving\add* YahwehВҰ198024.
\v 32 They were \add also\add* in charge of the sacredВҰ198044 tent and the holy placeВҰ198044 and assisting \add the priests\add* (their relatives, Aharon's descendantsВҰ198046) in their serviceВҰ198049 at Yahweh's temple.
\c 24
\s1 The Levites' duties
\rem /s1 The Work Assigned to the Priests; Duties of the Priests; Divisions of the Priests; The Divisions of Priests
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Aharon's sons were: Nadav, Avihu, EleazarВҰ198061, and ItamarВҰ198062,
\v 2 \add вүҲbut\add* Nadav and Avihu diedВҰ198064 \add вүҲbefore theirВҰ198068 fatherВҰ198068\add* and \add вүҲwithout having any children, so\add* \add only\add* EleazarВҰ198075 and ItamarВҰ198076 became priestsВҰ198074.\x + \xo 24:2: \xt Lev 10:1-2.\x*
\v 3 DavidВҰ198079 \add вүҲgave Eleazar'sВҰ198084 descendant TsadokВҰ198080, andВҰ198078 Itamar'sВҰ198089 descendant AhimelekВҰ198085 two different sets of dutiesВҰ198090 to perform\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲThere were more leaders among Eleazar's descendants than there were among Itamar's descendants, so they appointed sixteen leaders from Eleazar's descendants andВҰ198093 eightВҰ198117 from Itamar's descendants\add*.
\v 5 They dividedВҰ198119 up \add вүҲthe duties by lots so some of the leaders from each of the two groups served the facility andВҰ198119 others served God directly\add*. DOUBLE-CHECK, along with v3.
\v 6 Netanel'sВҰ198143 son ShemayahВҰ198140 was the LeviteВҰ198147 scribeВҰ198144 who recordedВҰ198139 all this in frontВҰ198148 of the kingВҰ198149 and the leaders, TsadokВҰ198151 the priest and Abiatar'sВҰ198156 son Ahimelek, and the clan leaders of the priestsВҰ198159 and the LevitesВҰ198147. (One familyВҰ198158 was drawn by lot from Eleazar'sВҰ198166 group, and then the next from Itamar'sВҰ198170, etc.)
\p
\v 7 The firstВҰ198175 two \add вүҲallocations of duties\add* wentВҰ198173 to Yehoyariv andВҰ198173 then YedayahВҰ198177.
\v 8 Next were Harim and SeorimВҰ198182,
\v 9 Malkiyyah and Miyyamin,
\v 10 Hakkots and Aviyyah,
\v 11 Yeshua and Shekanyah,
\v 12 Elyashiv and YakimВҰ198203,
\v 13 Huppah and Yesheveav,
\v 14 BilgahВҰ198214 and ImmerВҰ198217,
\v 15 Hezer and Ha-Pitstsets,
\v 16 Patahyah and Yehezkel,
\v 17 Yakin and GamulВҰ198237,
\v 18 Delayah and lastly, MaazyahВҰ198244.
\p
\v 19 Those \add were the priests\add* selected to \add be leaders of the groups\add* that would serve in Yahweh's temple, following the instructions that Yisrael's godВҰ198263 Yahweh had given theirВҰ198256 ancestor Aharon.
\s2 Other Levites
\rem /s1 The List of the Levites; Other Levites; Family Leaders among the Levites; The Rest of the Levites
\p
\v 20 This is a list of some of Levi'sВҰ198268 other descendants:
\li1 From Amram'sВҰ198271 sons: Shuvael.
\li1 From Shuvael's sons: YehdeyahВҰ198275.
\li1
\v 21 From Rehavyah's sonsВҰ198278: YishshiyahВҰ198281, the leader.
\li1
\v 22 From the Yitsharites: ShelomotВҰ198284.
\li1 From Shelomot'sВҰ198284 sonsВҰ198285: Yahat.
\li1
\v 23 \add Hevron's\add*\f + \fr 24:33 \ft Missing here in the Hebrew, but see \xt 1 Chr. 23:19.\f* sonsВҰ198289 \add вүҲ(in order)\add*: Yeriyyah, AmaryahВҰ198291, YahazielВҰ198293, Yekamean
\li1
\v 24 From Uzziel'sВҰ198299 sons: Mikah.
\li1 From Mikah's sons: ShamirВҰ198303.
\li1
\v 25 Mkah's younger brotherВҰ198306: Yishshiyah.
\li1 From Yishiyah's sonsВҰ198309: Zekaryah.
\li1
\v 26 Merari'sВҰ198314 sons: MahliВҰ198315 and MushiВҰ198316.
\li1 Yaaziyah's son: Beno.
\li1
\v 27 Merari'sВҰ198322 descendants through Yaaziyah: Beno, ShohamВҰ198325, Zakkur, and Ivri.
\li1
\v 28 From Mahli: EleazarВҰ198330 who had no sonsВҰ198335.
\li1
\v 29 Kish'sВҰ198340 son: Yerahme'el.
\li1
\v 30 Mushi'sВҰ198344 sons: MahliВҰ198345, EderВҰ198346, andВҰ198343 Yerimot.
\p Those were the LevitesВҰ198350 listed by theirВҰ198352 ancestors' families.
\v 31 They too, used lots just like Aharon's descendantsВҰ198362 (their relatives) \add to determine their specific duties\add* irrespective of where theyВҰ198357 came in their familiesВҰ198371. This was done in frontВҰ198365 of King DavidВҰ198366, TsadokВҰ198368 and Ahimelek, the clan leaders, and the \add other\add* priestsВҰ198372 and LevitesВҰ198373.
\c 25
\s1 The temple singers
\rem /s1 The Temple Musicians; Duties of the Musicians; The Singers
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then DavidВҰ198382 and the army chiefs allocated the \add musical\add* service to the sons of AsafВҰ198387, Heyman, and YedutunвҖ”the ones prophesyingВҰ198390 with harpsВҰ198394, with lyresВҰ198393, and with cymbalsВҰ198395. \add вүҲThis is a list of the menВҰ198398 whom they chose for that workВҰ198385\add*:
\li1
\v 2 From Asaf'sВҰ198403 sons: Zakkur, YosefВҰ198405, Netanyah, and AsarelahВҰ198407. They were supervised by Asaf, who prophesiedВҰ198414 \add вүҲunder the king's direction\add*.
\li1
\v 3 Six from Yedutun's family: GedalyahВҰ198423, TseriВҰ198424, YeshayahВҰ198425, Hashavyah, and MattityahВҰ198427. They were supervised by Yedutun, who prophesiedВҰ198434 with a harp, and thankedВҰ198437 and praisedВҰ198438 YahwehВҰ198439.
\li1
\v 4 From Heman'sВҰ198442 sonsВҰ198443: Bukkiyah, MattanyahВҰ198446, UzzielВҰ198447, Shuvael, Yerimot, HananyahВҰ198450, HananiВҰ198451, EliatahВҰ198452, GiddaltiВҰ198453, Romamti-Ezer, YoshbekashahВҰ198456, MallotiВҰ198457, HotirВҰ198458, and MahaziotВҰ198459.
\v 5 They were all sons of King David's prophet HemanВҰ198465 \add вүҲwho'd been promisedВҰ198468 by God that he'd strengthen him\add*, and God gave him fourteen sons and threeВҰ198479 daughtersВҰ198478.
\p
\v 6 All of those served as musiciansВҰ198488 in Yahweh's temple under theirВҰ198487 fathers' supervisionвҖ”they played cymbalsВҰ198491, harps, and lyres. \add вүҲTheir fathers were supervised by\add* the kingВҰ198499.
\v 7 There were 288 of those men andВҰ198519 theirВҰ198509 musical relativesВҰ198509 who played to YahwehВҰ198513.
\v 8 They used lots to determine their duties, whether young or old, andВҰ198521 \add вүҲirrespective of their musical abilities\add*.
\p
\v 9 The firstВҰ198535 allocation wentВҰ198533 (in order) to:
\li1 AsafВҰ198536 and his son YosefВҰ198537,
\li1 GedalyahВҰ198538 and his relativesВҰ198542 and sonsВҰ198543 (a total of twelve),
\li1
\v 10 ZakkurВҰ198548 and his sonsВҰ198549 and relativesВҰ198550 (another twelve),
\li1
\v 11 YitsriВҰ198555 and his sonsВҰ198556 and relativesВҰ198557 (twelve),
\li1
\v 12 NetanyahВҰ198562 and his sonsВҰ198563 and relativesВҰ198564 (twelve),
\li1
\v 13 BukkiyahВҰ198569 and his sonsВҰ198570 and relativesВҰ198571 (twelve),
\li1
\v 14 YesarelahВҰ198576 and his sonsВҰ198577 and relativesВҰ198578 (twelve),
\li1
\v 15 YeshayahВҰ198583 and his sonsВҰ198584 and relativesВҰ198585 (twelve),
\li1
\v 16 MattanyahВҰ198590 and his sonsВҰ198591 and relativesВҰ198592 (twelve),
\li1
\v 17 ShimeiВҰ198597 and his sonsВҰ198598 and relativesВҰ198599 (twelve),
\li1
\v 18 AzarelВҰ198606 and his sonsВҰ198607 and relativesВҰ198608 (twelve),
\li1
\v 19 HashavyahВҰ198614 and his sonsВҰ198615 and relativesВҰ198616 (twelve),
\li1
\v 20 ShuvaelВҰ198622 and his sonsВҰ198623 and relativesВҰ198624 (twelve),
\li1
\v 21 MattityahВҰ198630 and his sonsВҰ198631 and relativesВҰ198632 (twelve),
\li1
\v 22 YerimotВҰ198638 and his sonsВҰ198639 and relativesВҰ198640 (twelve),
\li1
\v 23 HanayahВҰ198646 and his sonsВҰ198647 and relativesВҰ198648 (twelve),
\li1
\v 24 YoshbekashahВҰ198654 and his sonsВҰ198655 and relativesВҰ198656 (twelve),
\li1
\v 25 HananiВҰ198662 and his sonsВҰ198663 and relativesВҰ198664 (twelve),
\li1
\v 26 MallotiВҰ198670 and his sonsВҰ198671 and relativesВҰ198672 (twelve),
\li1
\v 27 EliatahВҰ198677 and his sonsВҰ198678 and relativesВҰ198679 (twelve),
\li1
\v 28 HotirВҰ198685 and his sonsВҰ198686 and relativesВҰ198687 (twelve),
\li1
\v 29 GiddaltiВҰ198693 and his sonsВҰ198694 and relativesВҰ198695 (twelve),
\li1
\v 30 MahaziotВҰ198701 and his sonsВҰ198702 and relativesВҰ198703 (twelve),
\li1
\v 31 Romamti-Ezer and his sonsВҰ198711 and relativesВҰ198712 (twelve).
\c 26
\s1 The guards of doorway of temple
\rem /s1 The Gatekeepers; Duties of the Gatekeepers; The Temple Guards
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 These were the divisionВҰ198717 of the gatekeepersВҰ198718:
\li1 From the Korahites: Kore'sВҰ198723 son MeshelemyahВҰ198720 (Kore was one of Asaf'sВҰ198727 sonsВҰ198726),
\li1
\v 2 Meshelemyah's \add seven\add* sonsВҰ198730 (in order): Zekaryah, YediaelВҰ198733, ZebadyahВҰ198735, Yatniel,
\v 3 Eylam, YehohananВҰ198742, and Elyehoenai.
\li1
\v 4 Oved-Edom's \add eight\add* sonsВҰ198749 (in order): ShemayahВҰ198750, Yehozavad, YoahВҰ198754, SakarВҰ198756, NetanelВҰ198758,\x + \xo 26:4-5: \xt 2Sam 6:11; 1Ch 13:14.\x*
\v 5 Ammiel, Yissakar, and PeulletaiВҰ198765. (GodВҰ198769 had blessedВҰ198768 himВҰ198768.)
\li1
\v 6 Oved-Edom's son ShemayahВҰ198772 also had sonsВҰ198775. (They were leaders in theirВҰ198778 father's family because theyВҰ198783 were capable warriors.)
\v 7 Shemayah'sВҰ198786 sons were: OtniВҰ198787, RefaelВҰ198788, Oved, and Elzavad. His relatives ElihuВҰ198795 and Semakyah were also capable men.
\p
\v 8 All those descendants of Oved-EdomВҰ198804 and their sons and relativesВҰ198807 were capable people and strong workers. Altogether there were 62 of them.
\li1
\v 9 Meshelemyah had sons andВҰ198818 relativesВҰ198820 who were respected (eighteenВҰ198824 in total).
\li1
\v 10 Merari'sВҰ198833 descendantВҰ198831 Hosah'sВҰ198828 sonsВҰ198834: ShimriВҰ198835 (not actually the firstborn, but his fatherВҰ198843 appointed himВҰ198842 as the first),
\v 11 Hilkiyah, Tavalyah, and Zekaryah. (Thirteen total sonsВҰ198854 and relativesВҰ198855.)
\p
\v 12 Those men were leaders of the groups of men who guarded the gates of the temple. They worked in Yahweh's temple like theirВҰ198867 relativesВҰ198867 did.
\v 13 \add вүҲThey used lots to assign each family to a particular gate, irrespective of the family reputation\add*.
\v 14 Shelemyah'sВҰ198885 group was allocated to the easternВҰ198884 gate, and his son ZekaryahВҰ198886 (a wise adviser) was allocated to the northernВҰ198895 gate.
\v 15 Oved-Edom's group was allocated to the southernВҰ198900 gate, plus his sonsВҰ198901 \add were to guard\add* the storehousesВҰ198903.
\v 16 Shuppim'sВҰ198905 and Hosah'sВҰ198906 groups were allocated the western gate, along with the ShalleketВҰ198910 gate on the uphill road with \add вүҲside-by-side guards\add*.
\v 17 Every day there were six LevitesВҰ198918 on duty in the east, four in the northВҰ198920, four in the southВҰ198923, and two at the storehousesВҰ198926.
\v 18 There were fourВҰ198932 on the roadВҰ198933 by the western courtyard, and twoВҰ198934 in the courtyard.
\v 19 Those were the groups of men who were Korah's andВҰ198942 Merari'sВҰ198943 descendantsВҰ198940 who guarded the temple gates.
\s1 The guards of things/objects
\rem /s1 Other Temple Duties; The Treasurers and Other Officials; Treasurers and Other Officials; The Treasurers, Officers, and Judges
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 20 The Levite, Ahiyyah was \add вүҲin charge of\add* the temple treasuriesВҰ198952, as well as the storehousesВҰ198949 for dedicatedВҰ198953 giftsВҰ198953.
\v 21 Ladam's descendants (\add also\add* descendants of Gershon) \add вүҲwere leaders among their familyВҰ198961 groups. Yehiel was a descendant of this LadanВҰ198956\add*.
\v 22 Yehiel's sonsВҰ198966 were ZetamВҰ198968 and YoelВҰ198969, \add and they\add* \add вүҲwere in charge of\add* the storehousesВҰ198973 in Yahweh's temple.
\p
\v 23 \add Others who did that work\add* \add вүҲwere descendants of Amram, Yitshar, Hevron and Uzziel\add*.
\p
\v 24 Shuvael, a descendant of Mosheh'sВҰ198988 son GershomВҰ198985, was \add another\add* leader in charge of the treasuriesВҰ198992,
\v 25 along with his relativesВҰ198994: Eliezer'sВҰ198995 son Rehavyah, Rehavyah's son Yeshayah, Yeshayah'sВҰ198998 son Yoram, Yoram'sВҰ199000 son Zikri, andВҰ198994 Zikri'sВҰ199002 son ShelomotВҰ199004.
\v 26 ShelomotВҰ199009 and his relativesВҰ199010 \add вүҲsupervised\add* all the storehousesВҰ199014 for the sacred things thatВҰ199016 were consecratedВҰ199017 by King DavidВҰ199018, the \add вүҲclan leaders\add*, and the army division leaders and other commanders
\v 27 who had dedicated some of the plunder \add вүҲfrom their battlesВҰ199031\add* to the repairВҰ199036 of Yahweh'sВҰ199038 residence.
\v 28 Shelomot and his relativesВҰ199062 were also in charge of everythingВҰ199056 that the prophet Shemuel, \add King\add* ShaulВҰ199044 (Kish'sВҰ199047 son), and David's two army commanders AbnerВҰ199048 (Ner'sВҰ199051 son) and Yoav (Tseruyah's son) had dedicated \add to Yahweh\add*.
\s1 Other Levites' duties
\rem /s1 Duties of Other Levites
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 29 From Yitshar's descendants, KenanyahВҰ199066 and his sonsВҰ199067 worked outsideВҰ199069 \add the temple area\add* as officialsВҰ199073 and judgesВҰ199074 over YisraelВҰ199072.
\p
\v 30 From Hevron's descendants, Hashavyah and his relativesВҰ199078 were responsible for all the work done for YahwehВҰ199094 and for the kingВҰ199096 in the area west of the YordanВҰ199090 river. There were 1,700 of them \add вүҲwho were able to do their work well\add*.
\v 31 According to the records of Hevron's descendants, Yeriyyah was theirВҰ199102 leader. (In the fortiethВҰ199105 yearВҰ199104 of David'sВҰ199107 reignВҰ199106, theyВҰ199108 had searched \add ?in those records\add* andВҰ199109 discovered that there were powerful men in YazerВҰ199113 in GileadВҰ199114.)
\v 32 \add @Yeriyyah\add* had 2,700 relativesВҰ199116 who were strong \add workers\add* and \add вүҲleaders of their familiesВҰ199124\add*. King DavidВҰ199126 \add вүҲput them in charge of governing\add* the tribes of Reuven, Gad, and the eastern half of the tribe of Menashsheh, \add вүҲto ensure that all the people did what God commanded and what the king told them to do\add*.
\c 27
\s1 King David's officials
\rem /s1 The Military Divisions; Army Divisions; Military and Civil Organization; Military Commanders and Divisions
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 This is a list of the IsraeliВҰ199144 men who served the kingВҰ199157 \add in the army\add*. Some were leaders of familiesВҰ199148, some were commanders of divisions of one thousand, some were commanders of division of one hundredВҰ199152, and some were other officersВҰ199153. There were twenty-four thousand men in each group, and each group served one monthВҰ199167 each yearВҰ199168.
\li1
\v 2 Zavdiel's son Yashoveam, was in charge of the group that served during the first monthВҰ199179 each year.
\rem /s1 Administration of the Tribes of Israel
\v 3 \add He\add* was a descendantВҰ199193 of Perets and was the commanderВҰ199199 of all the \add вүҲarmy officers\add* during the firstВҰ199202 monthВҰ199201 \add each year\add*.
\li1
\v 4 DodaiВҰ199209 (the AhohitesВҰ199210) was the commander of the group that served during the secondВҰ199208 monthВҰ199207 each year. MiklotВҰ199212 was \add also\add* a leader in that group.
\li1
\v 5 BenayahВҰ199226, son of YehoyadaВҰ199229 the high priestВҰ199230, was the commanderВҰ199221 of the group that served during the third monthВҰ199224 each year.
\v 6 \add *He\add* was the strongest of вҖҳthe thirtyвҖҷ and was their leader. His son was Ammizavad.
\li1
\v 7 The fourth \add leader\add* for the fourth monthВҰ199251 was Yoav's brotherВҰ199256 Asahel, and then his son Zevadyah succeeded himВҰ199260. His divisionВҰ199262 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199265 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 8 The fifth \add leader\add* for the fifth monthВҰ199269 was the commanderВҰ199271 ShamhutВҰ199272 the Yizrahite. His divisionВҰ199275 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199278 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 9 The sixth \add leader\add* for the sixth monthВҰ199282 was Ikkesh'sВҰ199287 son IraВҰ199284 the TekoiteВҰ199288. His divisionВҰ199290 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199293 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 10 The seventh \add leader\add* for the seventh monthВҰ199297 was Helets the Peloite (an Eframite). His divisionВҰ199306 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199309 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 11 The eighth \add leader\add* for the eighth monthВҰ199313 was Sivkay the HushatiteВҰ199316 (a Zerahite). His divisionВҰ199319 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199322 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 12 The ninth \add leader\add* for the ninth monthВҰ199326 was Aviezer the AnatotiteВҰ199329 (a Benyamite). His divisionВҰ199333 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199336 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 13 The tenth \add leader\add* for the tenth monthВҰ199340 was MaharaiВҰ199342 the Netofatite (a Zerahite). His divisionВҰ199346 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199349 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 14 The eleventh \add leader\add* for the eleventh monthВҰ199358 was BenayahВҰ199359 the PiratoniteВҰ199360 (a Eframite). His divisionВҰ199366 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199369 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 15 The twelfth \add leader\add* for the twelfth monthВҰ199376 was HeldaiВҰ199377 the OtnielВҰ199379 (a Netofatite). His divisionВҰ199381 was twenty-four thousandВҰ199384 \add men\add*.
\s1 The teachers of Yisrael's descendants
\rem /s1 Officers of the Tribes; Leaders of the Tribes; Leaders of Tribes
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 16 There were certain tribal leaders over each of Yisrael's tribes:
\li1 Zikri'sВҰ199395 son EliezerВҰ199392 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* Revben.
\li1 Maakah's son Shefatyah was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* Shimeon.
\li1
\v 17 Kemuel'sВҰ199408 son Hashavyah was the leader of the Levites.
\li1 TsadokВҰ199410 was the leader of Aharon's descendants.
\li1
\v 18 David'sВҰ199416 \add older\add* brotherВҰ199415 ElihuВҰ199414 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* YehudahВҰ199413.
\li1 Mikael's son OmriВҰ199418 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* Yissakar.
\li1
\v 19 Ovadyah's son YishmayahВҰ199425 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* Zevulun.
\li1 Azriel'sВҰ199433 son Yerimot was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* NaftaliВҰ199429.
\li1
\v 20 Azazyah'sВҰ199441 son HosheaВҰ199438 was \add the leader of the tribeВҰ199443 of\add* EfrayimВҰ199437.
\li1 Pedayah'sВҰ199448 son YoelВҰ199445 was \add the leader of\add* the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ199444.
\li1
\v 21 Zekaryah's son Yiddo was \add the leader of\add* the half-tribe of Menashsheh in GileadВҰ199453.
\li1 Avner's son YaasielВҰ199460 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* BenyaminВҰ199459.
\li1
\v 22 Yeroham'sВҰ199470 son AzarelВҰ199467 was \add the leader of the tribe of\add* DanВҰ199466.
\m Those were the commandersВҰ199472 of Yisrael's tribes.
\p
\v 23 DavidВҰ199479 didn'tВҰ199476 include menВҰ199481 who were less than twentyВҰ199482 years old when he had ordered a censusВҰ199480, because YahwehВҰ199487 had promised that he would multiply the IsraelisВҰ199491 like starsВҰ199492 in the sky.\x + \xo 27:23: \xt Gen 15:5; 22:17; 26:4.\x*
\v 24 Yoav (Tseruyah's son) beganВҰ199499 the countВҰ199500 but never finishedВҰ199502 it because \add Yahweh's\add* angerВҰ199505 had struck YisraelВҰ199508, so the census result wasn't recorded in the record of King David'sВҰ199517 reign.\x + \xo 27:24: \xt 2Sam 24:15; 1Ch 21:1-14.\x*
\s1 King David's administrators
\rem /s1 Administrators of the Royal Property; Officials of David's Kingdom; Other Civic Officials; The King's Overseers
\s4 Full kingdom
\li1
\v 25 Adiel'sВҰ199526 son AzmavetВҰ199523 supervised the king's treasuries.
\li1 Uzziyah's son Yonatan was in charge of the storehouses in the countrysideВҰ199530 and in the citiesВҰ199531 and villagesВҰ199532, and in the watchtowers.
\rem /s1 David's Personal Advisers
\li1
\v 26 Keluv'sВҰ199549 son EzriВҰ199546 supervised the farm workers.
\li1
\v 27 ShimeiВҰ199554 the RamatiteВҰ199555 supervised the \add king's\add* vineyards.
\li1 ZavdiВҰ199560 the ShifmiteВҰ199561 supervised the wine \add вүҲvats\add*.
\li1
\v 28 BaalВҰ199570-HananВҰ199571 the GederiteВҰ199572 was over the olive groves and the sycamoreВҰ199567 treesВҰ199567 in the lowlands.
\li1 YoashВҰ199578 supervised the \add olive\add* oil \add вүҲstorage\add*.
\li1
\v 29 ShitraiВҰ199586 from the PlainВҰ199588 of SharonВҰ199585 was in charge of the herds \add of cattle\add* that grazed there.
\li1 Adlai'sВҰ199596 son ShafatВҰ199593 was in charge of the \add вүҲcattle\add* in the valleysВҰ199592.
\li1
\v 30 Ovil the YishmaeliteВҰ199603 was in charge of the camelsВҰ199601.
\li1 Yehdiyah the MeronotiteВҰ199608 was in charge of the donkeysВҰ199606.
\li1
\v 31 YazizВҰ199614 the HagriteВҰ199615 was in charge of the flocksВҰ199613 \add of sheep andВҰ199611 goats\add*.
\m All of those officialsВҰ199619 supervised King David'sВҰ199623 propertyВҰ199620.
\s1 King David's advisers
\s4 Full kingdom
\li1
\v 32 David'sВҰ199628 uncleВҰ199626 Yonatan was a \add вүҲwise adviser\add* andВҰ199625 a copyist.
\li1 Hakmoni's son Yehiel attended to the king'sВҰ199642 sonsВҰ199641.
\li1
\v 33 Ahitofel was the king's adviser.
\li1 HushaiВҰ199648 the Arkite was the king's friendВҰ199650.
\li1
\v 34 Ahitofel was succeeded by Benayah'sВҰ199658 son Yehoyada, thenВҰ199653 by Avyatar.
\li1 Yoav \add (Joab)\add* was the commanderВҰ199660 of the king's army.
\c 28
\s1 David's temple plans
\rem /s1 Solomon Instructed to Build the Temple; David's Instructions for the Temple; David's Plans for the Temple; David's Instructions to Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* DavidВҰ199668 called all Yisrael's leaders to assembleВҰ199667 in YerushalemВҰ199706: the tribal leaders, the leaders of the \add various\add* divisionsВҰ199678 that servedВҰ199679 the king, the commanders of army units of thousandsВҰ199684 and of hundredsВҰ199686, and the supervisors of all the propertyВҰ199690 and cattle belonging to the king and his sons, along with the tops officials, and the warriors including \add вүҲtheir powerful heroes\add*.
\p
\v 2 ThenВҰ199708 King DavidВҰ199709 stood up and spoke, вҖңListen to me, my brothersВҰ199716 and my peopleВҰ199717, I had in my heartВҰ199721 to put up a building for the box containing Yahweh's covenantВҰ199726 to rest in. It's the footstoolВҰ199729 of our god's feet of our god and I've made preparationsВҰ199732 to start building,\x + \xo 28:2-7: \xt 2Sam 7:1-16; 1Ch 17:1-14.\x*
\v 3 but GodВҰ199735 told me that I wouldn't be the one to buildВҰ199740 a houseВҰ199741 to \add вүҲhonour him\add* because I've \add вүҲbeen involved in a lot of war andВҰ199747 killings\add*.
\p
\v 4 вҖңYet Yisrael's godВҰ199752 YahwehВҰ199751 chose me from all of my father's family to be king over Yisrael foreverВҰ199764, because he chose a leaderВҰ199768 from \add the tribe of\add* YehudahВҰ199766, my father' tribe, andВҰ199750 among the sons of my father, with me he was pleasedВҰ199776 to make king over all IsraelВҰ199753.
\v 5 ThenВҰ199784 out of the many sons that he's givenВҰ199790 me, he choseВҰ199793 my son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ199794)\add* to \add вүҲbe the next king to rule his kingdomВҰ199800 of\add* YisraelВҰ199804.
\p
\v 6 вҖңThenВҰ199806 he told me, вҖҳYour son Shelomoh is the one who will buildВҰ199812 my temple and the courtyardsВҰ199814 \add around it\add*, because I've chosenВҰ199817 him to be like my son and I'll be like a fatherВҰ199825 to him.
\v 7 I'll establishВҰ199827 his kingdomВҰ199830 foreverВҰ199833, if he's diligent at following my instructions andВҰ199827 \add obeying\add* my judgements, like he is at present.вҖҷ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ199843\add* now, in \add вүҲfront\add* of all YisraelВҰ199847, Yahweh's assemblyВҰ199848, and in the ears of our god, \add I challenge you all to discover and obey\add* all the commandsВҰ199857 of your god Yahweh so that you'll all possessВҰ199861 the goodВҰ199865 land and you'll all leaveВҰ199866 your sons afterВҰ199868 you to inheritВҰ199866 it forever.
\p
\v 9 вҖңAnd you, Shelomoh my son, \add вүҲfollow\add* your father's godВҰ199881 and serveВҰ199883 him with a whole heartВҰ199884 and with a willingВҰ199887 life, because YahwehВҰ199893 \add вүҲlooks into\add* all heartsВҰ199891, and understandsВҰ199898 all \add вүҲyour motives\add*. If you look for him, he'll \add make sure\add* you find him, but if you abandonВҰ199906 him, he'll rejectВҰ199907 you forever.
\v 10 You can now see that you need to be strongВҰ199922 and get busy, because YahwehВҰ199915 has chosenВҰ199916 you to erect a buildingВҰ199918 to be his sanctuaryВҰ199921.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 Then DavidВҰ199927 gave the plans for \add the temple\add* to his son Shelomoh, \add including plans\add* for its porch, its houses, its treasuriesВҰ199937, its upperВҰ199938 rooms and its innerВҰ199940 rooms, and the \add вүҲroom to contain the sacred box\add*.
\v 12 \add He also handed over\add* the plans he envisioned for the temple courtyardsВҰ199950, all the surrounding apartments, all the treasuries, andВҰ199944 all the storerooms for sacred things.
\v 13 \add He included instructions\add* for the divisionsВҰ199964 of the priestsВҰ199965 and LevitesВҰ199966, for all the \add вүҲservices required to operate the temple, and for all the equipment and utensils needed for all that\add*.
\v 14 \add David had determined\add* the weight of goldВҰ199984 and silverВҰ199992 would be needed to make all the necessary items that would be used in the regular temple functions,
\v 15 \add including\add* the gold lampstands and lamps and the silverВҰ200011 lampstands and lamps,
\v 16 and the goldВҰ200021 for the display tables, and the silver for the silver tables.
\v 17 \add вүҲAlso\add* the pure gold meat forksВҰ200031 and the jugs and basinsВҰ200032, and the weights of the gold and silverВҰ200042 bowls.
\v 18 ThenВҰ200047 the weightВҰ200051 of refinedВҰ200050 gold for the incenseВҰ200048 altarВҰ200047, andВҰ200047 for making the winged creatures that spreadВҰ200056 out across the top of the box \add вүҲcontaining\add* Yahweh'sВҰ200063 agreement,
\v 19 \add saying\add*, вҖңI've written down all those plans \add вүҲwith Yahweh's direction as he gave me instructions for what has to be done\add*.вҖқ
\v 20 Then DavidВҰ200077 told his son Shelomoh, вҖңBe strongВҰ200080 and courageousВҰ200081, and \add вүҲget going\add*. Don't be afraidВҰ200085 or discouraged because Yahweh GodВҰ200091, my god, is with you. He won't leave you and he won't abandonВҰ200097 you untilВҰ200098 all the workВҰ200104 of \add вүҲconstructing\add* Yahweh's residence \add вүҲand the necessary equipment\add* is finishedВҰ200100.
\v 21 Listen, the divisionsВҰ200110 of the priestsВҰ200111 and the LevitesВҰ200112 for all the service of the god's houseВҰ200116 and all the \add вүҲskilledВҰ200125 workmen will be backing you in all the workВҰ200115\add*. The officialsВҰ200129 and all the peopleВҰ200132 are \add вүҲready to follow your instructions\add*.вҖқ
\c 29
\s1 Donations for the temple
\rem /s1 Gifts for Building the Temple; Solomon succeeds David as king; Offerings for Building the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then King DavidВҰ200139 told the entire assemblyВҰ200143, вҖңMy son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ200144)\add* \add вүҲhas been chosenВҰ200147 by God himself\add*. He's young and tender, and \add вүҲit's a hugeВҰ200154 job\add* because the templeВҰ200158 isn'tВҰ200156 being built for people, but for YahwehВҰ200160 God.\x + \xo 29:1-2: \xt 1Ch 22:5.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲI'veВҰ200166 used all my resources to provide a plentiful supply of materials\add* for my god's residence: the gold for the gold things, and the silver for the silver things, the bronze for the bronze things, the iron for the iron things, the wood for the wooden parts, onyx stones for inlays, antimonyВҰ200187 stones and colourfulВҰ200188 things, and all the rare stones and alabasterВҰ200194 stones.
\v 3 What's more, because I'm excited to have my god's residence \add built\add*, I've donated my own personal goldВҰ200205 andВҰ200206 silverВҰ200206 on top of everything else that I've preparedВҰ200214 for the sacredВҰ200216 temple:
\v 4 100 tonnes of gold and 2,500 tonnes of refinedВҰ200229 silverВҰ200228 for overlayingВҰ200230 the buildings' wallsВҰ200231,
\v 5 \add as well as\add* gold for the gold things, silver for the silver things, and for everything \add вүҲto be made\add* by the craftsmenВҰ200242. \add вүҲSo\add* who is willing today, \add вүҲto commit themselves\add* to makingВҰ200244 a contributionВҰ200244 towards Yahweh's work?
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ200256 the familyВҰ200252 leaders and the leaders of the \add вүҲtribesВҰ200255\add*, and the \add вүҲvarious levels of military\add* commandersВҰ200257, and the king'sВҰ200262 \add вүҲconstruction overseers\add*, \add all\add* contributed willinglyВҰ200250.
\v 7 TheyВҰ200268 donated \add a total of\add* 170 tonnes of gold and 100kg of gold coins, 350 tonnes of silverВҰ200276, 600 tonnes of bronzeВҰ200280, and 3,400 tonnes of iron for the \add вүҲtemple\add* construction,
\v 8 plus anyone who had precious stonesВҰ200293 donated them to the treasuryВҰ200295 for the \add вүҲtemple\add*. Yehiel (a Gershonite) \add вүҲwas in charge of those\add*.
\v 9 The peopleВҰ200306 were \add вүҲexcited\add*, becauseВҰ200307 they'dВҰ200313 \add all\add* givenВҰ200309 willinglyВҰ200309 to YahwehВҰ200314, andВҰ200315 King DavidВҰ200316 was also very pleased.
\s1 The praying for David
\rem /s1 David's Prayer of Praise; David's Praise to God; David Praises God; David's Prayer
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 10 Then \add King\add* DavidВҰ200324 blessed Yahweh in \add вүҲfront of\add* the entireВҰ200329 assemblyВҰ200331, saying, вҖңBlessed are youВҰ200335, Yahweh, GodВҰ200337 of YisraelВҰ200338, ourВҰ200339 fatherВҰ200339, from the ages past and until the ages to come.
\v 11 Greatness and the powerВҰ200348, beauty and splendour and majestyВҰ200351 \add all belong\add* to you, Yahweh, as indeed does everythingВҰ200354 in the heavensВҰ200355 and on the earthВҰ200356. The kingdomВҰ200359 and \add вүҲsupreme leadership\add* \add all belongs\add* to you, Yahweh.\x + \xo 29:11: \xt Mat 6:13.\x*
\v 12 Wealth and \add prestige comes from you\add*, and you rule over everything. \add вүҲYou have the powerВҰ200372 and strength and control\add* to make \add people\add* greatВҰ200375 and to strengthen everyone,
\v 13 \add вүҲso\add* now, our godВҰ200380, we're thankingВҰ200381 you andВҰ200379 praisingВҰ200384 yourВҰ200386 beautiful nameВҰ200385.
\p
\v 14 ButВҰ200388 who am I, and who are my peopleВҰ200392, that we should \add вүҲbe in a position to be able\add* to donate freely like this? \add вүҲYes,\add* everythingВҰ200402 comes from you, and \add вүҲwe've simply givenВҰ200404 back from what you gaveВҰ200404 to us\add*,
\v 15 because we're \add just\add* strangers on the earth \add вүҲin yourВҰ200411 eyes\add*, and foreign guests like all our ancestorsВҰ200415. Our time on the earth is like a shadowВҰ200416 \add вүҲwithout any permanence\add*.
\v 16 YahwehВҰ200425 our godВҰ200426, all this abundanceВҰ200428 thatВҰ200430 we have \add вүҲcollected\add* in order to buildВҰ200432 a houseВҰ200435 for you, for your holy nameВҰ200436, \add вүҲoriginally it came from you and it all belongs to you\add* \add anyway\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲYes\add* I knowВҰ200444, my godВҰ200445, that you examine our hearts and you'reВҰ200447 pleasedВҰ200451 \add вүҲwhen we do what is right\add*. I have freely offered all theseВҰ200458 \add gifts\add* \add вүҲas I strive to do what is right\add*, and now \add вүҲI'm also happy to\add* see your peopleВҰ200460 to freely offer \add gifts\add* to you.
\v 18 YahwehВҰ200470, the godВҰ200471 of our ancestorsВҰ200475 AbrahamВҰ200472, Yitshak \add (IsaacВҰ200473)\add*, and YisraelВҰ200474 \add (IsraelВҰ200474)\add*, \add help yourВҰ200483 peopleВҰ200483 continue to desire to do things like this foreverВҰ200479, and help them remain loyal to youВҰ200486\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲAlso,\add* giveВҰ200490 my son Shelomoh \add (Solomon)\add* a \add вүҲsincere desire\add* to follow your instructions, your testimonies, and your regulationsВҰ200496, and to do \add вүҲeverything needed\add* to buildВҰ200499 the templeВҰ200500 \add вүҲfollowing all my preparationВҰ200503 work\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 Then DavidВҰ200507 told all the assembled \add people\add*, вҖңBless yourВҰ200517 godВҰ200517 Yahweh.вҖқ and the entireВҰ200519 assembly blessedВҰ200511 Yahweh, the god of theirВҰ200524 ancestorsВҰ200524. Then they bowedВҰ200525 down to \add вүҲhonour\add* \add both\add* Yahweh and the kingВҰ200528.
\rem /s1 Solomon Named as King; Solomon Acknowledged as King
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ200530 they offered sacrifices to Yahweh, and sacrificed burntВҰ200535 offerings to Yahweh on the following day: 1,000 bullsВҰ200540, 1,000 rams, 1,000 lambsВҰ200544, plus theirВҰ200546 drinkВҰ200546 offerings and sacrifices for all YisraelВҰ200551 in abundance.
\v 22 They ateВҰ200553 and drankВҰ200554 \add вүҲin Yahweh's honour\add* that dayВҰ200557 with greatВҰ200560 celebration.
\rem /s1 Solomon Anointed King
\p ThenВҰ200553 they rededicated David'sВҰ200566 son Shelomoh \add (SolomonВҰ200563)\add* as kingВҰ200561, and anointedВҰ200567 him as leader \add вүҲon Yahweh's behalf\add* and TsadokВҰ200570 as priestВҰ200571.
\v 23 Shelomoh satВҰ200573 on Yahweh's throneВҰ200577 as kingВҰ200580 \add вүҲreplacing\add* his fatherВҰ200584 DavidВҰ200583, and he prosperedВҰ200585 and all YisraelВҰ200590 listened to him.\x + \xo 29:23: \xt 1Ki 2:12.\x*
